1
00:00:00,317 --> 00:00:01,992
Did everyone dress well?

2
00:00:03,618 --> 00:00:06,478
- Last week, Loco...
- That's right.

3
00:00:07,246 --> 00:00:09,928
Loco, your zipper says "0."

4
00:00:10,684 --> 00:00:13,271
- I'll go with zero.
- You mean it?

5
00:00:15,260 --> 00:00:16,521
- 0 people?
- 0 people!

6
00:00:16,546 --> 00:00:18,793
- No one changed?
- Seriously?

7
00:00:19,248 --> 00:00:21,264
It's shocking that no
one changed their identity.

8
00:00:21,387 --> 00:00:24,648
Anyway, do you all remember
what happened last week, right?

9
00:00:24,673 --> 00:00:25,929
- Of course.
- Absolutely.

10
00:00:25,954 --> 00:00:29,471
They were given an unprecedented
dating method for 24 hours.

11
00:00:29,496 --> 00:00:30,727
They have full freedom.

12
00:00:31,621 --> 00:00:34,067
(For 24 hours, until
the final selection, all

13
00:00:34,092 --> 00:00:36,803
participants may go on as
many dates as they want.)

14
00:00:36,828 --> 00:00:38,728
We have full freedom for 24 hours?

15
00:00:38,976 --> 00:00:40,182
We don't need to sleep?

16
00:00:40,383 --> 00:00:42,628
For real? It's really just like that?

17
00:00:43,096 --> 00:00:44,592
Wow, what is this?

18
00:00:44,617 --> 00:00:47,880
As soon as it happened,
Su-won ran out of the room.

19
00:00:48,741 --> 00:00:51,042
I don't bother with texts.
I'll head there right away.

20
00:00:51,411 --> 00:00:54,910
I assume he went to see Ha-neul.

21
00:00:54,935 --> 00:00:56,962
- Right.
- That's probably right.

22
00:00:56,987 --> 00:00:59,202
Honestly, won't Ha-neul be touched?

23
00:01:00,531 --> 00:01:01,641
I hope so.

24
00:01:02,351 --> 00:01:07,184
(Remaining time until the final selection)

25
00:01:08,733 --> 00:01:10,745
(Everyone got a text.)

26
00:01:10,770 --> 00:01:12,827
"Ask the one you're
interested in on a date."

27
00:01:12,852 --> 00:01:16,170
"You can use your phone or
ask them directly face to face."

28
00:01:16,413 --> 00:01:19,056
I think phones will play a huge variable.

29
00:01:19,081 --> 00:01:22,928
Right. Even if you're already on a date,
you can get a call from someone else.

30
00:01:24,067 --> 00:01:26,925
Hang on. Why am I so nervous?

31
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:29,683
(Complicated)

32
00:01:31,542 --> 00:01:33,463
(Stand)

33
00:01:34,165 --> 00:01:36,720
I don't bother with texts.
I'll head there right away.

34
00:01:36,843 --> 00:01:38,494
Gosh, what a manly man.

35
00:01:39,306 --> 00:01:41,084
Aren't you gonna take your phone?

36
00:01:41,952 --> 00:01:43,873
- He didn't take it.
- "I don't need it."

37
00:01:45,472 --> 00:01:49,313
Oh, he's going there right away.
He's not hesitating this time.

38
00:01:49,338 --> 00:01:51,063
He's going straight forward.

39
00:01:51,574 --> 00:01:53,121
(Women's lodging)

40
00:01:54,664 --> 00:01:56,211
Ha-neul.

41
00:01:56,386 --> 00:01:57,735
(Startled)

42
00:01:58,118 --> 00:01:59,452
Come here for a sec.

43
00:02:00,138 --> 00:02:01,741
What the heck?

44
00:02:02,130 --> 00:02:03,518
"Ha-neul."

45
00:02:06,501 --> 00:02:08,434
Do you... want to go outside with me?

46
00:02:09,533 --> 00:02:12,133
- Right now?
- He wants to go out now?

47
00:02:13,437 --> 00:02:15,374
I came here to ask you directly.

48
00:02:18,028 --> 00:02:19,028
Let's go.

49
00:02:19,236 --> 00:02:21,546
"Sure." She'll say yes, right?

50
00:02:22,661 --> 00:02:24,018
- Let me get my bag.
- Okay.

51
00:02:25,632 --> 00:02:27,068
I'm so annoyed!

52
00:02:29,484 --> 00:02:31,467
Oh, they're wondering
if they should contact

53
00:02:31,896 --> 00:02:34,606
the guy first or if they
should wait for him.

54
00:02:39,377 --> 00:02:40,757
- What was that?
- Huh?

55
00:02:41,075 --> 00:02:42,075
What was that?

56
00:02:42,245 --> 00:02:43,300
He wants to go on a date.

57
00:02:43,325 --> 00:02:44,969
- When?
- Right now.

58
00:02:44,994 --> 00:02:47,368
You're so lucky! I bet you
guys are going for a drive!

59
00:02:48,316 --> 00:02:49,916
I should just go to bed.

60
00:02:50,729 --> 00:02:51,841
I'm gonna sleep.

61
00:02:51,866 --> 00:02:53,230
(Envious)

62
00:02:55,925 --> 00:02:57,815
Everyone's just holding onto their phones.

63
00:02:59,663 --> 00:03:04,947
(The clock is ticking, and their
thoughts grow more complex.)

64
00:03:06,127 --> 00:03:07,548
Who will make a move first?

65
00:03:10,169 --> 00:03:13,055
(Just then, an alarm breaks the
silence in the women's dorm.)

66
00:03:14,086 --> 00:03:16,057
(Is Yeo-min the one who got the message?)

67
00:03:16,946 --> 00:03:18,930
(Shift)

68
00:03:18,955 --> 00:03:20,690
I guess it was Da-na's phone.

69
00:03:21,354 --> 00:03:23,921
(Won-jae: Wanna go see the stars?)

70
00:03:24,567 --> 00:03:27,204
Wow! There are so many
stars in the sky tonight.

71
00:03:27,711 --> 00:03:30,394
- Do you like stargazing?
- Yeah.

72
00:03:31,131 --> 00:03:32,504
He remembered that.

73
00:03:32,529 --> 00:03:35,370
(Won-jae remembered what Da-Na said.)

74
00:03:36,343 --> 00:03:37,343
Goodness.

75
00:03:39,067 --> 00:03:42,456
(She received 0 messages...)

76
00:03:43,987 --> 00:03:46,954
Da-Na, you look like you're
going through a lot right now.

77
00:03:48,348 --> 00:03:49,348
(Close)

78
00:03:51,915 --> 00:03:53,573
What is she agonizing over?

79
00:03:55,154 --> 00:03:56,845
Won-jae texted me.

80
00:03:57,139 --> 00:03:59,126
You don't want to go on a date with him?

81
00:03:59,847 --> 00:04:01,264
(So that's what happened.)

82
00:04:01,289 --> 00:04:04,028
Is that why Yeo-min left the room?

83
00:04:04,499 --> 00:04:05,808
Yeo-min...

84
00:04:07,328 --> 00:04:09,261
I think it will be worrisome.

85
00:04:12,723 --> 00:04:14,270
How could this be?

86
00:04:14,590 --> 00:04:15,629
Who got texts?

87
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:23,660
What about you, Da-Na?

88
00:04:24,876 --> 00:04:26,646
- I got one.
- From who?

89
00:04:26,908 --> 00:04:27,908
Won-jae.

90
00:04:31,171 --> 00:04:32,238
What did he say?

91
00:04:34,128 --> 00:04:37,698
- It's not like she can stay silent.
- It's vague to lie, too.

92
00:04:39,146 --> 00:04:40,560
He wants to go stargazing.

93
00:04:40,997 --> 00:04:42,935
That's wonderful!

94
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,762
That's so romantic.

95
00:04:45,674 --> 00:04:47,042
(Embarrassed)

96
00:04:47,067 --> 00:04:50,451
She can't keep it a secret
because they're in the same room.

97
00:04:53,702 --> 00:04:56,750
Should we think about it
some more? It just started.

98
00:04:56,894 --> 00:04:59,086
- Of course. We have plenty of time.
- Yeah.

99
00:05:02,522 --> 00:05:06,190
- Even if Da-Na might be happy, she
can't really express it. - Yeah.

100
00:05:06,787 --> 00:05:08,041
It must be uncomfortable.

101
00:05:08,756 --> 00:05:10,295
I really don't know what to do.

102
00:05:11,405 --> 00:05:12,405
I'm off.

103
00:05:13,785 --> 00:05:15,333
You're going somewhere right now?

104
00:05:15,358 --> 00:05:16,358
(Bow)

105
00:05:16,383 --> 00:05:18,877
- Wow!
- He's relaxed.

106
00:05:19,078 --> 00:05:20,078
I'm off.

107
00:05:21,229 --> 00:05:22,335
Have a safe trip.

108
00:05:22,893 --> 00:05:26,115
Won-jae's about to head right
out as soon as he gets a reply.

109
00:05:26,140 --> 00:05:30,858
Su-won's quick ability to act
makes the other guys feel uneasy.)

110
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:33,229
I'm going out.

111
00:05:34,317 --> 00:05:36,832
- Ji-min, too?
- You are? Right now?

112
00:05:38,607 --> 00:05:40,543
Did he send a text?
Is he going on a date?

113
00:05:40,568 --> 00:05:41,632
(Wary)

114
00:05:42,889 --> 00:05:43,889
He's quick.

115
00:05:45,382 --> 00:05:46,770
(Stand)

116
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:52,079
Won-jae's nervous.

117
00:05:53,026 --> 00:05:56,218
(Ji-min is in front of the women's dorm.)

118
00:05:56,243 --> 00:05:59,149
(Who is he waiting for?)

119
00:05:59,701 --> 00:06:02,978
(Soon, Won-jae rushes out
with obscure nervousness.)

120
00:06:03,687 --> 00:06:05,864
- Oh no.
- They keep bumping into each other.

121
00:06:07,009 --> 00:06:10,327
- He asked her where she is.
- They both texted Da-Na.

122
00:06:12,221 --> 00:06:14,135
(Two guys are asking one girl on a date.)

123
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,427
What should she do?

124
00:06:15,452 --> 00:06:16,867
I'm sure she's in a dilemma.

125
00:06:19,882 --> 00:06:21,914
I guess she didn't reply.

126
00:06:22,683 --> 00:06:24,272
You can't relax then.

127
00:06:24,297 --> 00:06:26,376
- You've got to be aggressive.
- Yeah.

128
00:06:31,264 --> 00:06:32,264
Is it Won-jae?

129
00:06:32,803 --> 00:06:34,097
Pick up the phone. Pick up!

130
00:06:35,812 --> 00:06:37,549
- Hello?
- Hello?

131
00:06:37,874 --> 00:06:39,565
- Hey.
- Where are you?

132
00:06:39,590 --> 00:06:41,981
I'm brushing my teeth in the dressing room.

133
00:06:43,025 --> 00:06:46,072
Do you want to go stargazing?

134
00:06:46,797 --> 00:06:49,329
(Let's go stargazing.)

135
00:06:49,637 --> 00:06:52,889
(He's bravely asking her
out for the second time.)

136
00:06:52,914 --> 00:06:55,288
- Do you want to go stargazing?
- Sure.

137
00:06:56,404 --> 00:06:58,039
- Should we go now?
- Yeah.

138
00:06:58,629 --> 00:07:01,025
(Wide grin)

139
00:07:01,415 --> 00:07:03,925
- Alright, call me when you're ready.
- Okay.

140
00:07:10,733 --> 00:07:13,951
(Da-Na picked Won-jae, not Ji-min.)

141
00:07:13,976 --> 00:07:16,470
Gosh, you should've been a bit faster!

142
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:19,346
Ji-min's in a stew right now.

143
00:07:22,119 --> 00:07:23,719
The timing is important.

144
00:07:24,364 --> 00:07:26,538
Calling is better than
texting and personally

145
00:07:26,563 --> 00:07:28,474
visiting them is better than calling.

146
00:07:30,345 --> 00:07:31,345
This is tough.

147
00:07:31,557 --> 00:07:33,235
This is your biggest opportunity.

148
00:07:33,260 --> 00:07:35,101
They said we can date everyone.

149
00:07:35,126 --> 00:07:36,722
Oh, really?

150
00:07:37,287 --> 00:07:38,287
Freely?

151
00:07:39,242 --> 00:07:41,361
They're giving us time
to figure things out.

152
00:07:41,913 --> 00:07:44,833
Gosh, it's already episode 7,
but he's figuring things out now?

153
00:07:44,858 --> 00:07:48,032
We'll invite Jae-hyung
when we have a 50-episode

154
00:07:48,057 --> 00:07:51,036
program and slowly set
up some plans with him.

155
00:07:51,061 --> 00:07:52,183
"50-episode program."

156
00:07:52,208 --> 00:07:53,851
Then I'll go after you guys.

157
00:07:56,197 --> 00:07:59,467
Who will Jae-hyung ask on a date?

158
00:07:59,861 --> 00:08:02,805
He said he'll go after all the guys.

159
00:08:03,078 --> 00:08:06,722
I think he's going to pick someone
who didn't get asked on a date.

160
00:08:06,747 --> 00:08:09,439
- That's what it feels like.
- Yeah.

161
00:08:12,243 --> 00:08:16,303
(What is their last date like
before the final selection?)

162
00:08:16,791 --> 00:08:18,307
They need to have good conversations.

163
00:08:18,697 --> 00:08:21,222
Oh, I guess this is it. It's pretty.

164
00:08:22,253 --> 00:08:25,185
(Final date: Su-won & Ha-neul)

165
00:08:26,832 --> 00:08:27,832
Hello.

166
00:08:28,660 --> 00:08:31,525
- What do you want?
- I'm not gonna eat a lot.

167
00:08:31,550 --> 00:08:33,758
We'll take the one with six of them.

168
00:08:35,682 --> 00:08:37,898
- They look delicious.
- Thank you.

169
00:08:38,112 --> 00:08:39,231
Thank you.

170
00:08:40,554 --> 00:08:41,998
It's nice.

171
00:08:43,826 --> 00:08:44,826
Let's eat.

172
00:08:45,461 --> 00:08:46,859
I haven't had these in a while.

173
00:08:47,887 --> 00:08:51,196
- What are these crumbs called?
- Katsuobushi.

174
00:08:52,051 --> 00:08:53,510
You really are in the food industry.

175
00:08:53,535 --> 00:08:56,814
Oh! So if you know what "katsuobushi
is," you're in the food industry!

176
00:08:56,839 --> 00:08:58,975
Is that what he thinks?

177
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:02,725
- What are these crumbs called?
- Katsuobushi.

178
00:09:03,403 --> 00:09:04,855
You really are in the food industry.

179
00:09:06,119 --> 00:09:07,302
You're well-informed.

180
00:09:07,905 --> 00:09:09,709
Who doesn't know "katsuobushi"?

181
00:09:10,069 --> 00:09:12,521
It's better if you eat it yourself
than if I feed you, right?

182
00:09:12,546 --> 00:09:14,085
- Eat it, okay?
- Okay.

183
00:09:14,883 --> 00:09:18,192
I think that Su-won is really
not good at expressing himself.

184
00:09:18,656 --> 00:09:20,322
- Wow, there's steam.
- Yeah.

185
00:09:21,604 --> 00:09:23,540
(Nom)

186
00:09:27,830 --> 00:09:30,596
(However, he's always
paying attention to her.)

187
00:09:31,189 --> 00:09:34,353
(With his efforts, will Ha-neul
open her heart again?)

188
00:09:34,655 --> 00:09:35,958
(Glance)

189
00:09:37,884 --> 00:09:40,987
- It kind of feels like they've made up.
- Their gazes...

190
00:09:42,047 --> 00:09:44,866
- Have you ever been in a
long-distance relationship? - No.

191
00:09:45,234 --> 00:09:46,234
Su-won is...

192
00:09:46,259 --> 00:09:49,346
He's in Changwon, and she's in Seoul.

193
00:09:49,784 --> 00:09:52,373
(There's about 370
kilometers between them.)

194
00:09:52,398 --> 00:09:54,678
I saw my previous
boyfriends almost every day.

195
00:09:54,703 --> 00:09:56,646
Every day? How is that possible?

196
00:09:56,992 --> 00:09:58,603
If they work at a company...

197
00:09:58,628 --> 00:10:00,825
I've never dated someone
with that kind of job.

198
00:10:00,850 --> 00:10:01,850
Oh, really?

199
00:10:02,895 --> 00:10:06,841
(Su-won is new to Ha-neul because he
lives far away and works at a company.)

200
00:10:07,626 --> 00:10:09,211
I have a question.

201
00:10:09,236 --> 00:10:12,207
Let's say you're in a long-distance
relationship but you guys fought.

202
00:10:12,538 --> 00:10:13,968
How do you solve it?

203
00:10:15,942 --> 00:10:16,942
Fight?

204
00:10:17,397 --> 00:10:19,539
They both seem like they
want to date each other.

205
00:10:20,035 --> 00:10:23,193
We can't help but talk then. I'll
go up to see her on the weekend.

206
00:10:23,218 --> 00:10:25,312
Wow, sounds tough.

207
00:10:28,289 --> 00:10:31,106
You seem burdened by the idea
of a long-distance relationship.

208
00:10:34,076 --> 00:10:37,525
- Is your place closer to Seoul Station
or Suseo Station? - I'm not sure.

209
00:10:38,499 --> 00:10:43,724
If I take a train to Seoul after
work on Friday, I'll arrive around 9 p.m.

210
00:10:45,854 --> 00:10:49,618
That's very detailed. He's so ready.

211
00:10:49,908 --> 00:10:52,360
They don't care about Love
Catchers or Money Catchers.

212
00:10:52,656 --> 00:10:57,284
What they want to figure out is if they'll
meet at Seoul Station or Suseo Station.

213
00:10:57,309 --> 00:10:59,430
It seems like they've
already started dating.

214
00:11:00,070 --> 00:11:02,426
Long-distance relationships are manageable.

215
00:11:02,451 --> 00:11:03,745
- Su-won.
- What?

216
00:11:04,031 --> 00:11:05,547
Focus on the game.

217
00:11:06,193 --> 00:11:08,079
(The cute office worker
keeps trying to appeal

218
00:11:08,104 --> 00:11:09,789
to her about long-distance
relationships.)

219
00:11:09,814 --> 00:11:12,426
- Was I getting too ahead of myself? Sorry.
- Yeah.

220
00:11:13,202 --> 00:11:14,575
Was I overdoing it?

221
00:11:17,429 --> 00:11:20,754
- But isn't it nice to see that?
- It's adorable.

222
00:11:20,923 --> 00:11:24,272
He's already drawing
out their future together.

223
00:11:24,297 --> 00:11:26,490
I think it will be
heart-fluttering and nice.

224
00:11:28,917 --> 00:11:30,679
Do you regret coming on this show?

225
00:11:31,650 --> 00:11:34,840
I don't. Not really.

226
00:11:35,933 --> 00:11:41,300
But I think I'm experiencing
deeper feelings than expected.

227
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:43,652
So I was pretty amazed.

228
00:11:43,677 --> 00:11:47,544
It's like, "Oh, this is
happening. It's really happening."

229
00:11:49,821 --> 00:11:56,323
(He feels unexpected emotions. Is he
a Love Catcher? Or a Money Catcher?)

230
00:11:56,999 --> 00:11:59,622
(What is the truth that is
hidden behind the excitement?)

231
00:11:59,647 --> 00:12:02,869
After getting some fresh air at the
Han River, are you not upset anymore?

232
00:12:03,684 --> 00:12:05,858
Do you feel better now?

233
00:12:09,410 --> 00:12:11,210
The takoyaki was good.

234
00:12:11,732 --> 00:12:12,732
Really?

235
00:12:14,146 --> 00:12:17,671
Today was a really good day.

236
00:12:20,630 --> 00:12:22,693
I think they've made up now.

237
00:12:23,029 --> 00:12:24,989
(Mindful)

238
00:12:25,014 --> 00:12:28,255
Do we look alike? I don't
think we do. Or maybe we do.

239
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:30,089
- What do you mean?
- I'm talking about us.

240
00:12:30,997 --> 00:12:34,466
- Oh my goodness!
- She's saying they look alike.

241
00:12:34,491 --> 00:12:37,723
- The color of their tops are the same.
- They do look alike.

242
00:12:38,191 --> 00:12:40,839
We have big eyes. You have a sharper nose.

243
00:12:41,410 --> 00:12:43,180
(Smile)

244
00:12:43,862 --> 00:12:46,306
(On their way back to the lodging)

245
00:12:46,331 --> 00:12:51,739
But I felt like Ji-min was
totally treating me like a friend.

246
00:12:51,764 --> 00:12:55,822
He wasn't. I'm telling you,
he was interested in you.

247
00:12:56,667 --> 00:12:57,667
I'm sure of it.

248
00:12:58,224 --> 00:12:59,224
Really?

249
00:12:59,804 --> 00:13:01,071
I never felt that.

250
00:13:02,003 --> 00:13:03,315
Not even once.

251
00:13:04,448 --> 00:13:05,448
Oh.

252
00:13:06,139 --> 00:13:09,260
Isn't Ha-neul saying, "I had no
idea he liked me, and we were

253
00:13:09,285 --> 00:13:12,204
just talking. So there's nothing
you have to worry about."

254
00:13:12,229 --> 00:13:13,589
I think so.

255
00:13:13,614 --> 00:13:15,678
(Meanwhile, what's happening
at the Love Mansion?)

256
00:13:15,703 --> 00:13:17,681
Are you for sure not
going to contact anyone?

257
00:13:17,706 --> 00:13:19,922
- Who would I contact?
- Won-jae.

258
00:13:19,947 --> 00:13:22,480
I don't know when their date will end.

259
00:13:22,790 --> 00:13:25,450
- That's why you feel sad?
- Yeah.

260
00:13:27,181 --> 00:13:32,376
(Everyone was given 24 hours, but
there's nothing these two can do...)

261
00:13:34,921 --> 00:13:37,477
This is hurting my pride. I can't do it.

262
00:13:37,502 --> 00:13:39,829
- Why are you crying?
- Oh dear.

263
00:13:40,205 --> 00:13:42,578
Go ahead and sit there.

264
00:13:46,042 --> 00:13:49,332
(All this time, she's been telling
herself, "It's okay. I have a chance."

265
00:13:50,133 --> 00:13:52,971
(Today, it has hit her
that she's complete alone.)

266
00:13:54,140 --> 00:13:57,101
Don't cry. Don't cry.

267
00:13:57,126 --> 00:14:00,685
This is hurting my pride. I can't do it.

268
00:14:00,710 --> 00:14:04,150
It's okay. It's okay.

269
00:14:07,417 --> 00:14:08,790
Suddenly...

270
00:14:09,298 --> 00:14:12,571
Everything is happening
between the people in this house,

271
00:14:12,596 --> 00:14:14,764
but since it ended like this...

272
00:14:14,789 --> 00:14:18,698
Right, right. It's upsetting, isn't it?

273
00:14:18,723 --> 00:14:23,575
- I feel like I'm not attractive enough.
- No way. That's not true.

274
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:26,546
(Pat)

275
00:14:26,571 --> 00:14:29,453
He didn't even consider me.

276
00:14:29,807 --> 00:14:31,940
He had already made up his mind.

277
00:14:34,257 --> 00:14:41,655
I'm not sad over the fact
that he ended up liking someone else.

278
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:45,224
It's just that this
situation keeps repeating.

279
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:50,983
I started to pity myself.

280
00:14:52,051 --> 00:14:53,385
So I was very upset.

281
00:14:54,928 --> 00:14:58,112
When things are confusing or
ambiguous, you still have hope.

282
00:14:58,137 --> 00:15:02,075
But she can see that Won-jae
is clearly going for Da-Na.

283
00:15:04,772 --> 00:15:06,866
I think the sky got clearer after the rain.

284
00:15:10,110 --> 00:15:12,126
- Are you okay with stargazing?
- Yeah, I like it.

285
00:15:13,161 --> 00:15:14,161
I do.

286
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:18,569
- I feel like we're escaping in
the middle of the night. - Yeah.

287
00:15:19,713 --> 00:15:22,421
(Rooftop)

288
00:15:22,446 --> 00:15:24,921
- It's so beautiful.
- The moon nowadays is really pretty.

289
00:15:24,946 --> 00:15:25,946
Yeah.

290
00:15:25,971 --> 00:15:27,771
Has the moon changed recently?

291
00:15:28,462 --> 00:15:31,150
He said the moon nowadays is pretty.

292
00:15:31,693 --> 00:15:35,495
I thought we wouldn't be able to come here
because it was raining earlier. Thank God.

293
00:15:37,382 --> 00:15:40,216
- It's nice to be out.
- Yeah.

294
00:15:40,822 --> 00:15:43,711
- Look at the stars.
- There are so many of them.

295
00:15:44,542 --> 00:15:46,581
- That one at the very
top is a satellite, right?

296
00:15:46,606 --> 00:15:50,440
The sparkly thing, you mean? Yeah.

297
00:15:51,483 --> 00:15:54,666
(The moment their dream comes true.)

298
00:15:55,273 --> 00:15:57,051
It's really beautiful.

299
00:15:58,850 --> 00:16:01,318
What's with this couple?
It's like a youth drama.

300
00:16:01,343 --> 00:16:03,423
- What's going on?
- It's really like a drama.

301
00:16:05,967 --> 00:16:07,880
It's nice to get some fresh air.

302
00:16:08,287 --> 00:16:10,207
(Happy)

303
00:16:10,322 --> 00:16:12,560
Wow, look at his eyes.
They’re dripping with affection.

304
00:16:12,585 --> 00:16:14,546
He looks so excited.

305
00:16:16,837 --> 00:16:18,455
It's nice to get some fresh air.

306
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:21,854
(Da-na's happiness is Won-jae's joy.)

307
00:16:25,878 --> 00:16:27,973
What do you think?
Are you glad you came out?

308
00:16:30,803 --> 00:16:32,096
(Nod)

309
00:16:32,121 --> 00:16:33,121
I'm glad.

310
00:16:36,024 --> 00:16:38,825
- He can't look at her.
- Oh my gosh! He's so shy!

311
00:16:38,850 --> 00:16:41,320
(I support this couple!)

312
00:16:43,969 --> 00:16:46,904
One week is really short.

313
00:16:47,934 --> 00:16:51,393
It's too short to get to know someone new.

314
00:16:52,391 --> 00:16:55,390
It's also too short to
start a new relationship.

315
00:16:55,752 --> 00:17:03,124
But I think I spent most
of this short time with you.

316
00:17:03,441 --> 00:17:04,441
That's true.

317
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:07,675
We danced together, too.

318
00:17:08,405 --> 00:17:10,630
He must have really liked that.

319
00:17:10,865 --> 00:17:15,246
I gave you an invitation the
next day, and we went on a date.

320
00:17:16,130 --> 00:17:19,488
So we relatively spent
quite a bit of time together.

321
00:17:19,513 --> 00:17:24,530
Despite that, I wanted to spend
some more time with you.

322
00:17:26,473 --> 00:17:27,473
Thanks.

323
00:17:29,128 --> 00:17:30,666
(What does "thanks" mean?)

324
00:17:30,691 --> 00:17:35,495
Before coming here, she
probably read Ji-min's text.

325
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:36,880
- She probably did.
- Yeah.

326
00:17:36,905 --> 00:17:39,837
She looks happy, but it
seems complicated, too.

327
00:17:39,862 --> 00:17:42,593
I think she kind of felt sorry
when she said "thanks."

328
00:17:42,618 --> 00:17:47,421
It felt like she had more to
say after that, but she didn't.

329
00:17:47,627 --> 00:17:50,645
What he wants to hear is "I like
you, too" rather than "thank you."

330
00:17:50,670 --> 00:17:52,070
That's what he wants.

331
00:17:53,161 --> 00:17:56,216
(At that time, the Love Mansion is empty.)

332
00:17:56,515 --> 00:18:02,277
Won-jae, it's sad that this is the last
day. Can we talk during lunch tomorrow?)

333
00:18:03,272 --> 00:18:06,933
(She hesitates to press the "send" button.)

334
00:18:07,396 --> 00:18:09,039
(Thinking)

335
00:18:10,251 --> 00:18:11,631
(Send)

336
00:18:12,754 --> 00:18:16,339
(Yeo-min mustered up her final courage.)

337
00:18:17,672 --> 00:18:21,455
(Will her sincerity reach him?)

338
00:18:23,399 --> 00:18:24,399
(Ding)

339
00:18:25,833 --> 00:18:26,935
What do we do?

340
00:18:27,502 --> 00:18:30,126
(However, Won-jae doesn't
check Yeo-min's text.)

341
00:18:30,151 --> 00:18:32,930
- Anyway, that's how I felt.
- He's not looking at it.

342
00:18:33,472 --> 00:18:35,369
- Check your text.
- I can do it later.

343
00:18:35,849 --> 00:18:38,888
Wow, he's really only looking at her.

344
00:18:42,079 --> 00:18:43,822
(Stare)

345
00:18:48,238 --> 00:18:51,234
(All she can do is wait.)

346
00:18:51,259 --> 00:18:54,182
- It took her a lot of courage
to send that. - Oh no.

347
00:18:54,207 --> 00:18:57,701
(She can't let go of the phone...)

348
00:18:59,958 --> 00:19:04,397
(How does Yeo-min feel right now...?)

349
00:19:05,435 --> 00:19:06,808
My first impression of you...

350
00:19:07,574 --> 00:19:09,405
Do you remember what I said?

351
00:19:10,830 --> 00:19:14,775
- You know how you saw all the
girls on the first day? - Yes.

352
00:19:14,928 --> 00:19:18,303
What were your first impressions of the?
I'm so curious. Did you already say it?

353
00:19:18,482 --> 00:19:20,977
My first impression
of Da-Na was that she

354
00:19:21,002 --> 00:19:23,674
had milky skin and
prominent facial features.

355
00:19:23,956 --> 00:19:25,558
And I thought she was tall.

356
00:19:26,392 --> 00:19:28,815
So she left a big impression.

357
00:19:29,168 --> 00:19:32,646
The first impression
of you that I said earlier.

358
00:19:33,281 --> 00:19:38,735
That's actually my ideal type.

359
00:19:40,458 --> 00:19:41,790
You're honest.

360
00:19:42,417 --> 00:19:44,158
Thanks for thinking that I'm pretty.

361
00:19:46,813 --> 00:19:49,249
You really are pretty.

362
00:19:50,939 --> 00:19:52,539
"You really are pretty."

363
00:19:52,899 --> 00:19:53,899
Oh my god!

364
00:19:53,924 --> 00:19:56,368
I kind of had a feeling he would say this.

365
00:19:57,109 --> 00:19:58,576
You really are pretty.

366
00:19:59,159 --> 00:20:00,961
(Burying her face)

367
00:20:01,377 --> 00:20:04,844
(Da-Na is too
embarrassed to lift her face.)

368
00:20:05,039 --> 00:20:06,305
The moon is pretty.

369
00:20:06,918 --> 00:20:10,375
The... The moon is pretty.

370
00:20:11,109 --> 00:20:13,506
- It's really pretty.
- It's pretty.

371
00:20:14,366 --> 00:20:16,644
- The stars are beautiful, too.
- Yeah.

372
00:20:16,669 --> 00:20:20,265
Everything's pretty here.
There's nothing that isn't pretty.

373
00:20:21,405 --> 00:20:24,764
Their conversation is like
something from a fairy tale.

374
00:20:24,789 --> 00:20:26,256
Wow, that was awesome.

375
00:20:27,379 --> 00:20:29,046
Anyway, that's how it is.

376
00:20:30,264 --> 00:20:32,494
So we were given 24
hours for our last mission.

377
00:20:32,519 --> 00:20:33,519
Right.

378
00:20:34,173 --> 00:20:36,736
Personally, I want to...

379
00:20:39,775 --> 00:20:42,576
spend the remaining 21 hours with you.

380
00:20:43,743 --> 00:20:45,032
(So many great lines!)

381
00:20:45,057 --> 00:20:46,772
He's saying a lot of great lines.

382
00:20:46,805 --> 00:20:49,671
I want to spend the
remaining 21 hours with you.

383
00:20:50,563 --> 00:20:52,963
That's personally what I want to do.

384
00:20:55,719 --> 00:20:56,822
Yeah. That's how I feel.

385
00:20:56,847 --> 00:20:59,070
I think he has expressed
his heart in every way he can.

386
00:21:00,304 --> 00:21:03,486
- It depends on how Da-Na accepts it.
- Right.

387
00:21:06,119 --> 00:21:10,144
After you called me, Ji-min texted me.

388
00:21:10,505 --> 00:21:11,505
So...

389
00:21:12,547 --> 00:21:14,642
when I have time...

390
00:21:15,443 --> 00:21:18,955
(Da-Na can't give all of
her 24 hours to Won-jae.)

391
00:21:19,482 --> 00:21:22,149
Then after you get plenty of rest...

392
00:21:24,372 --> 00:21:28,297
meet Ji-min as soon as you can

393
00:21:32,941 --> 00:21:34,926
Then I'll ask you out on another date.

394
00:21:36,453 --> 00:21:40,555
And when I do, say yes.

395
00:21:42,403 --> 00:21:43,990
Does she have to promise him now?

396
00:21:44,015 --> 00:21:45,960
(Da-Na is hesitating...?)

397
00:21:46,446 --> 00:21:48,295
(Anxious)

398
00:21:48,719 --> 00:21:50,235
- Okay.
- Okay.

399
00:21:51,012 --> 00:21:52,084
- You mean it?
- Yeah.

400
00:21:54,143 --> 00:21:56,796
(Will they be able to have
their last date as he wishes?)

401
00:21:56,821 --> 00:21:57,821
Should we go?

402
00:21:58,786 --> 00:22:01,723
But there was something
odd about their conversation.

403
00:22:01,748 --> 00:22:07,665
Da-Na gave short answers,
and her expression was stiff.

404
00:22:07,690 --> 00:22:11,144
- She did seem to have a lot on her mind.
- It's making me nervous.

405
00:22:12,769 --> 00:22:17,403
(Remaining time until the final selection)

406
00:22:17,428 --> 00:22:21,369
(Ji-min hasn't fallen asleep yet.)

407
00:22:21,394 --> 00:22:24,223
He didn't get an answer from Da-Na yet.

408
00:22:26,442 --> 00:22:28,053
He's waiting for her.

409
00:22:29,704 --> 00:22:32,135
He won't be able to sleep then.

410
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:35,378
(He keeps checking his
phone even though it didn't ring.)

411
00:22:36,713 --> 00:22:37,713
(Peek)

412
00:22:38,648 --> 00:22:42,495
(It's a long night where he's waiting
for an answer that's not coming.)

413
00:22:46,728 --> 00:22:49,316
(Da-Na, you're in the
middle of a date, so don't reply.)

414
00:22:49,341 --> 00:22:51,663
(Let's go on a
date at noon tomorrow.)

415
00:22:51,688 --> 00:22:55,047
Wait a minute. It's 4:15 a.m.

416
00:22:55,072 --> 00:22:57,194
- He couldn't sleep!
- Oh my god. You're right.

417
00:22:57,219 --> 00:23:00,268
She was stargazing with
Won-jae till then. Wow.

418
00:23:00,958 --> 00:23:06,479
(Ji-min's night was full of the
cell phone light instead of stars.)

419
00:23:08,326 --> 00:23:09,890
- Go in. Thanks.
- Good night.

420
00:23:12,025 --> 00:23:14,870
(Won-jae came home at dawn.)

421
00:23:15,799 --> 00:23:16,799
(Glance)

422
00:23:19,496 --> 00:23:21,337
Ji-min will know that he just came.

423
00:23:28,434 --> 00:23:30,148
(Spring)

424
00:23:32,915 --> 00:23:35,280
- He's going.
- He's super anxious.

425
00:23:36,338 --> 00:23:39,070
(Ji-min goes out right away.)

426
00:23:41,211 --> 00:23:43,378
- He's calling her?
- He's in a hurry.

427
00:23:44,129 --> 00:23:47,214
(Da-Na hasn't fallen asleep yet.)

428
00:23:47,726 --> 00:23:49,859
- Hello?
- You're awake?

429
00:23:50,682 --> 00:23:53,698
- Yeah. Are you in your room?
- Yes.

430
00:23:54,281 --> 00:23:57,400
- Can we talk for a minute?
- Sure.

431
00:23:57,768 --> 00:23:59,299
- Bye.
- Bye.

432
00:24:00,726 --> 00:24:04,168
(It hasn't even been five minutes since
she's been home but she's going out again.)

433
00:24:05,211 --> 00:24:07,520
- Should we go down?
- Sure.

434
00:24:12,243 --> 00:24:14,976
Oh no! Won-jae saw that his bed is empty!

435
00:24:15,277 --> 00:24:16,499
Goodness.

436
00:24:16,787 --> 00:24:19,096
Gosh, now Won-jae
won't be able to sleep.

437
00:24:19,560 --> 00:24:21,392
No one is at peace tonight.

438
00:24:21,417 --> 00:24:24,237
(He can't sleep on the last night
because his nerves are on the edge.)

439
00:24:25,473 --> 00:24:27,604
(Won-jae replied to Yeo-min's text.)

440
00:24:27,629 --> 00:24:29,162
Uh-oh, she fell asleep.

441
00:24:29,187 --> 00:24:31,682
(However, Yeo-min fell asleep
after waiting for a long time.)

442
00:24:32,379 --> 00:24:34,827
(It's early dawn, and the
sun is already coming up.)

443
00:24:34,852 --> 00:24:36,973
- I wanted to go on a date with you.
- I see.

444
00:24:38,008 --> 00:24:41,946
You didn't reply, so I didn't
know how to prepare for it.

445
00:24:42,965 --> 00:24:46,053
I was distressed, and there was a
lot on my mind, so I couldn't sleep.

446
00:24:47,256 --> 00:24:48,842
So I'm curious.

447
00:24:51,973 --> 00:24:54,573
- It's bright.
- The sun's already up.

448
00:25:00,658 --> 00:25:02,825
I haven't felt like this in a while.

449
00:25:04,933 --> 00:25:07,028
I don't know what I should do.

450
00:25:07,992 --> 00:25:10,897
But it's true that I want
to spend time with you.

451
00:25:12,187 --> 00:25:13,879
I want to talk with you more.

452
00:25:15,070 --> 00:25:16,979
You didn't answer,

453
00:25:17,856 --> 00:25:21,676
so I thought maybe that was your way
of telling me you were uncomfortable.

454
00:25:21,701 --> 00:25:23,999
No, it's just that it was late.

455
00:25:24,024 --> 00:25:27,662
Right. So I had a lot on my mind.

456
00:25:28,474 --> 00:25:30,874
It was late, but I still called you.

457
00:25:31,931 --> 00:25:34,288
How do you feel? Do you
have a lot on your mind, too?

458
00:25:35,320 --> 00:25:38,975
(Who is Da-na's heart leaning towards?)

459
00:25:39,065 --> 00:25:40,732
Yeah, I do.

460
00:25:45,431 --> 00:25:49,716
I heard you've narrowed down your choices.

461
00:25:49,741 --> 00:25:51,036
Yeah.

462
00:25:53,207 --> 00:25:54,636
Can I ask you who they are?

463
00:25:56,132 --> 00:25:59,600
(A careful but straightforward question)

464
00:26:00,175 --> 00:26:01,548
Won-jae and you.

465
00:26:03,207 --> 00:26:07,427
(Is that a good thing...
or a bad thing...?)

466
00:26:07,787 --> 00:26:10,391
I must have been concerned
that Da-Na went on a date

467
00:26:10,416 --> 00:26:13,067
with another guy because
I didn't get a wink of sleep.

468
00:26:14,715 --> 00:26:16,524
I didn't know...

469
00:26:19,183 --> 00:26:20,424
who she liked.

470
00:26:20,449 --> 00:26:23,325
I kept thinking that it wasn't me.

471
00:26:24,631 --> 00:26:26,590
But I wanted one last chance with her.

472
00:26:27,435 --> 00:26:30,085
You have plans tomorrow, right?

473
00:26:30,740 --> 00:26:33,192
Tomorrow... um...

474
00:26:34,242 --> 00:26:35,642
Tomorrow afternoon...

475
00:26:35,941 --> 00:26:37,387
Do you want to meet up at noon?

476
00:26:38,914 --> 00:26:41,248
Is that okay? Isn't that too early?

477
00:26:41,529 --> 00:26:44,262
I'll send you a text when I wake up then.

478
00:26:44,639 --> 00:26:46,419
- Is that better? - Yeah.

479
00:26:48,628 --> 00:26:51,330
The sun is coming
up. Let's go inside.

480
00:26:52,254 --> 00:27:00,046
The way he's suddenly giving her attention
makes me think he's a Money Catcher.

481
00:27:00,071 --> 00:27:01,579
- Really?
- Yes.

482
00:27:01,604 --> 00:27:04,883
Seeing him in such a rush makes
me think he's a Love Catcher actually.

483
00:27:04,908 --> 00:27:07,070
I thought he was a
Money Catcher at first, too.

484
00:27:07,438 --> 00:27:13,434
But the way he kept checking
his phone over and over again

485
00:27:13,673 --> 00:27:16,142
made him look like someone who's in love.

486
00:27:16,167 --> 00:27:18,161
But if you think about
it another way, he

487
00:27:18,186 --> 00:27:20,322
looks like someone
who's desperate for money.

488
00:27:21,277 --> 00:27:26,841
That sounded kind of harsh, and Money
Catchers here are just players in the game.

489
00:27:27,093 --> 00:27:30,634
But if you think about the money, you
can go crazy. It's impossible to sleep.

490
00:27:31,327 --> 00:27:34,297
- "My $50,000!"
- "My money! My money!"

491
00:27:34,866 --> 00:27:38,219
(Roaring with laughter)

492
00:27:38,383 --> 00:27:41,289
It seems like everything worked out
between Su-won and Ha-neul, right?

493
00:27:41,314 --> 00:27:42,513
Yes.

494
00:27:42,545 --> 00:27:44,862
They both seem like Love Catchers to me.

495
00:27:44,887 --> 00:27:47,239
Really? I wrote down that
she's a Money Catcher.

496
00:27:47,264 --> 00:27:48,580
- Really?
- Yes.

497
00:27:48,612 --> 00:27:50,466
During the date,

498
00:27:50,491 --> 00:27:56,524
I felt like Su-won was really
excited about their conversation.

499
00:27:56,824 --> 00:28:01,498
But the more they talked
about it, the sorrier she looked.

500
00:28:01,539 --> 00:28:07,148
What I thought was that she
still thinks he's a Money Catcher.

501
00:28:07,173 --> 00:28:11,508
- I thought so, too.
- She's still a bit wary of him.

502
00:28:12,595 --> 00:28:15,802
(Remaining time until the final selection)

503
00:28:15,827 --> 00:28:18,438
- There's not much time left.
- There are only 14 hours left.

504
00:28:19,031 --> 00:28:22,390
(The last morning at Love Mansion)

505
00:28:22,915 --> 00:28:25,961
(Men's dorm)

506
00:28:28,790 --> 00:28:30,950
Where was Jae-hyung yesterday?

507
00:28:31,517 --> 00:28:32,819
(Spring)

508
00:28:33,775 --> 00:28:35,298
He got up right away.

509
00:28:35,626 --> 00:28:37,959
Everyone's waking up together.

510
00:28:37,984 --> 00:28:40,051
Did someone hit a gong outside?

511
00:28:40,646 --> 00:28:44,368
Did someone taser them?
How could everyone get up at once?

512
00:28:44,393 --> 00:28:47,001
That's how you usually
get up in the military.

513
00:28:47,638 --> 00:28:49,940
What kind of devices
did you put in their beds?

514
00:28:52,180 --> 00:28:53,466
(Startled)

515
00:28:54,032 --> 00:28:56,215
Didn't you say that you
were leaving early today?

516
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:57,551
10 o'clock.

517
00:28:59,189 --> 00:29:00,760
(Humming)

518
00:29:01,450 --> 00:29:04,510
(He's already excited
preparing for the date.)

519
00:29:05,315 --> 00:29:09,649
I'm looking forward to having conversations
with her that will bring us closer.

520
00:29:10,210 --> 00:29:11,543
It's an important date.

521
00:29:11,575 --> 00:29:15,375
I want to talk with Ha-neul
so that there are no regrets.

522
00:29:15,905 --> 00:29:18,828
- I want to make a good choice.
- He really seems like a Love Catcher.

523
00:29:20,674 --> 00:29:22,356
I'm half-nervous, half-excited.

524
00:29:23,932 --> 00:29:28,615
I want to let Da-Na know that
my feelings are sincere.

525
00:29:29,144 --> 00:29:32,667
Oh my. Seeing them get ready
for their dates makes my heart race.

526
00:29:33,504 --> 00:29:35,179
(Spray)

527
00:29:35,204 --> 00:29:36,695
What is he doing?

528
00:29:39,039 --> 00:29:41,462
- He's spraying a lot.
- He's spraying a lot.

529
00:29:41,487 --> 00:29:44,719
What do you think about guys
who are salted in cologne like that?

530
00:29:46,009 --> 00:29:47,405
- Salted in cologne?
- Yeah.

531
00:29:47,430 --> 00:29:51,821
We know what kind of
day it is. It's the last date.

532
00:29:51,846 --> 00:29:54,540
- That would be cute then.
- I think it'd be cute.

533
00:29:55,238 --> 00:29:57,970
(Women's dorm)

534
00:29:58,801 --> 00:30:00,475
(No one is moving.)

535
00:30:01,402 --> 00:30:03,541
(Yeo-min fell asleep
waiting for Won-jae's answer.)

536
00:30:03,573 --> 00:30:04,988
Did Yeo-min see his reply?

537
00:30:05,448 --> 00:30:06,448
Her phone.

538
00:30:08,421 --> 00:30:11,871
(I have plans with Da-Na again
tomorrow... I don't know when we're

539
00:30:11,896 --> 00:30:15,241
meeting or where we're going.
Would it be okay to go for a walk?)

540
00:30:16,946 --> 00:30:19,685
Yeo-min could get really heartbroken.

541
00:30:25,272 --> 00:30:28,066
(After much thinking,
she sent her answer.)

542
00:30:30,630 --> 00:30:36,662
(Sure, let's do that.)

543
00:30:38,295 --> 00:30:39,558
I was upset.

544
00:30:40,480 --> 00:30:45,250
This situation was pitiful.

545
00:30:47,964 --> 00:30:49,964
I get it.

546
00:30:49,989 --> 00:30:55,261
(The last day is so cruel.)

547
00:30:57,013 --> 00:30:58,909
I feel so bad for her.

548
00:31:01,649 --> 00:31:04,589
(To someone else,
this is their last chance.)

549
00:31:04,614 --> 00:31:06,768
- Oh, it's Jae-hyung.
- Finally, it's him.

550
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:08,747
Where is he going?

551
00:31:09,122 --> 00:31:11,003
I actually thought about it a lot.

552
00:31:14,946 --> 00:31:18,128
We didn't really have
a chance to talk.

553
00:31:18,375 --> 00:31:19,440
Who can it be?

554
00:31:20,443 --> 00:31:24,038
I thought I should use this
opportunity to talk with her more.

555
00:31:26,289 --> 00:31:28,059
He's putting a lot of
effort into this look.

556
00:31:28,084 --> 00:31:29,727
Who is he going on a date with?

557
00:31:30,247 --> 00:31:32,112
I can't bring myself to say it.

558
00:31:32,320 --> 00:31:33,708
Why not?

559
00:31:34,687 --> 00:31:38,181
It's nothing. I can't
say it in this situation.

560
00:31:38,206 --> 00:31:39,842
Why not? I don't get it.

561
00:31:39,867 --> 00:31:42,771
(Except for Jae-hyung,
everyone was confused.)

562
00:31:42,796 --> 00:31:44,998
I've never really talked
with In-seong before.

563
00:31:46,254 --> 00:31:49,382
- So I was going to try talking with her.
- Oh, really?

564
00:31:49,546 --> 00:31:50,680
Oh, it's In-seong.

565
00:31:51,214 --> 00:31:53,391
That's right. They didn't
really communicate.

566
00:31:53,416 --> 00:31:55,144
Is Jae-hyung a Money Catcher?

567
00:31:56,179 --> 00:31:57,972
I'm gonna go get some fresh air.

568
00:32:00,438 --> 00:32:04,469
I was thinking I should
bring it up this afternoon.

569
00:32:04,855 --> 00:32:06,728
This is new.

570
00:32:06,945 --> 00:32:09,739
But did the guys feel
like they couldn't approach

571
00:32:09,764 --> 00:32:12,278
me because it's obvious
who I would end up with?

572
00:32:13,077 --> 00:32:15,508
-Because of Jung-woo?
- Yeah, there was something like that.

573
00:32:15,533 --> 00:32:17,738
Really? I see.

574
00:32:19,831 --> 00:32:21,981
But then something happened then.

575
00:32:22,388 --> 00:32:24,460
So it kept getting tangled up.

576
00:32:24,670 --> 00:32:26,866
Yes, but then...

577
00:32:28,302 --> 00:32:29,863
he ended up getting eliminated.

578
00:32:30,294 --> 00:32:32,119
And there was an opening.

579
00:32:34,241 --> 00:32:38,609
- That has to do with timing, too.
- Right. If you look at it that way.

580
00:32:38,985 --> 00:32:41,263
That's true.

581
00:32:41,898 --> 00:32:44,657
(Are Jae-hyung and In-seong
Love Catchers that finally met?)

582
00:32:44,965 --> 00:32:47,957
(Or are they Money Catchers
who have no other choice?)

583
00:32:47,982 --> 00:32:50,745
Tomorrow...

584
00:32:51,652 --> 00:32:54,121
(Tomorrow?)

585
00:32:54,949 --> 00:32:56,394
Do you want to go to the beach?

586
00:32:57,508 --> 00:32:59,308
He mustered up the courage.

587
00:32:59,757 --> 00:33:01,313
Sure, sounds good.

588
00:33:01,338 --> 00:33:04,680
- Then let's go to the beach tomorrow.
- Okay. That's fine with me.

589
00:33:04,705 --> 00:33:06,160
Oh, as expected.

590
00:33:07,013 --> 00:33:10,407
(Jae-hyung's last date is In-seong.)

591
00:33:10,432 --> 00:33:12,363
Jae-hyung put his bangs back down.

592
00:33:13,804 --> 00:33:17,495
He blocked Da-Na from his heart,
and he blocked his forehead, too.

593
00:33:20,365 --> 00:33:21,765
(Knock, knock, knock)

594
00:33:26,199 --> 00:33:27,732
- Hi, Jae-hyung.
- Hi.

595
00:33:28,613 --> 00:33:30,279
Oh, we kind of match.

596
00:33:30,885 --> 00:33:32,718
That's true. They're both wearing shirts.

597
00:33:32,743 --> 00:33:34,197
How cool is that?

598
00:33:35,192 --> 00:33:37,493
We all discussed our
dates, and ours is the best.

599
00:33:37,518 --> 00:33:39,661
- Right. We're the best.
- We're No. 1.

600
00:33:40,403 --> 00:33:43,077
- Shall we go?
- Let's go.

601
00:33:43,741 --> 00:33:47,629
Isn't the weather so beautiful?
It's the perfect day for the beach.

602
00:33:50,350 --> 00:33:53,225
(There's another couple going on a date.)

603
00:33:53,250 --> 00:33:54,949
He's like a model.

604
00:33:58,486 --> 00:34:00,906
- Ha-neul!
- She's dressed up.

605
00:34:01,909 --> 00:34:03,234
Did you sleep well?

606
00:34:05,016 --> 00:34:07,875
They're back to being the couple
we saw in the very beginning.

607
00:34:07,900 --> 00:34:10,542
- It's been a while since
we've seen that. - Let's go.

608
00:34:10,567 --> 00:34:13,029
- Are the other girls sleeping?
- No.

609
00:34:13,680 --> 00:34:16,740
(Ji-min is ready to go.)

610
00:34:16,765 --> 00:34:18,949
Relax. Relax.

611
00:34:19,698 --> 00:34:21,508
Just relax. Relax.

612
00:34:22,872 --> 00:34:26,139
(It's the first time Ji-min looks nervous.)

613
00:34:32,140 --> 00:34:34,005
- Da-Na?
- Yes?

614
00:34:35,293 --> 00:34:36,602
(Dash)

615
00:34:39,219 --> 00:34:42,569
- They look so good together.
- Did they all plan to match?

616
00:34:42,594 --> 00:34:44,722
They're all gorgeous couples.

617
00:34:46,229 --> 00:34:49,910
(And there are people
who couldn't go on dates.)

618
00:34:50,644 --> 00:34:51,977
The weather is nice.

619
00:34:52,334 --> 00:34:53,890
It's a really beautiful day.

620
00:34:55,028 --> 00:34:57,410
It would've been amazing
if we had gone out for a date.

621
00:34:59,059 --> 00:35:01,701
(This is Yeo-min's last chance.)

622
00:35:01,726 --> 00:35:03,664
Gosh, they look so good together.

623
00:35:06,008 --> 00:35:07,341
It's really too bad.

624
00:35:08,394 --> 00:35:10,403
It's too bad that it's
already the last day.

625
00:35:10,428 --> 00:35:11,428
Yeah.

626
00:35:13,009 --> 00:35:16,121
It's unfortunate that we never
got to go on a proper date.

627
00:35:16,577 --> 00:35:22,309
I wanted to take this chance
to get some things off my chest.

628
00:35:22,334 --> 00:35:24,837
- We only got to talk on that first day.
- I know.

629
00:35:26,190 --> 00:35:28,674
You should've gone on a date with me today.

630
00:35:30,035 --> 00:35:32,289
It's the last day. You could go with me.

631
00:35:33,118 --> 00:35:34,586
I'm sure it's regrettable.

632
00:35:35,168 --> 00:35:40,049
Da-Na and I had already made
plans before I got your text.

633
00:35:40,594 --> 00:35:42,284
(Disappointed)

634
00:35:42,467 --> 00:35:44,556
- Was I late again?
- Huh?

635
00:35:44,763 --> 00:35:46,225
Was I late again?

636
00:35:46,726 --> 00:35:48,402
I guess I was late this time, too.

637
00:35:49,461 --> 00:35:50,861
I shouldn't hesitate.

638
00:35:51,643 --> 00:35:53,907
If I want to spend time
with you, I shouldn't hesitate.

639
00:35:56,834 --> 00:35:57,969
It's hard.

640
00:35:59,048 --> 00:36:00,342
That's right. It's tough.

641
00:36:00,367 --> 00:36:02,774
It's all because I think too much.

642
00:36:05,025 --> 00:36:07,128
It took me a while to text you, too.

643
00:36:07,536 --> 00:36:10,821
- Really? - It took a long time
to figure how to ask you.

644
00:36:11,151 --> 00:36:14,945
You were with Da-Na, so I
thought it'd be rude to text you.

645
00:36:14,970 --> 00:36:16,766
Oh, you knew I was out?

646
00:36:17,744 --> 00:36:18,966
How could I not?

647
00:36:18,991 --> 00:36:22,818
You contacted Da-Na as
soon as you got a phone.

648
00:36:24,235 --> 00:36:25,886
So how could I not know?

649
00:36:27,501 --> 00:36:34,855
- Everything just happened at once.
- Right.

650
00:36:34,880 --> 00:36:41,082
I never knew that my heart
could change so quickly.

651
00:36:41,492 --> 00:36:43,525
But you can't help it
because of the circumstances.

652
00:36:43,550 --> 00:36:45,899
That's why it's important
to get the timing right.

653
00:36:46,012 --> 00:36:48,536
I'm the one who got missed it. Not you.

654
00:36:49,234 --> 00:36:51,697
(Won-jae is also confused.)

655
00:36:52,976 --> 00:36:54,310
I missed the timing.

656
00:36:54,760 --> 00:36:56,775
Gosh, she's blaming herself.

657
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:58,148
(Sorry)

658
00:36:58,876 --> 00:36:59,978
To be honest...

659
00:37:01,912 --> 00:37:03,535
I was dumped by my ex-boyfriends.

660
00:37:04,039 --> 00:37:08,483
I gave them my all, but
they ended things with me.

661
00:37:08,686 --> 00:37:11,703
I always got hurt, so I was a bit...

662
00:37:13,454 --> 00:37:16,721
I didn't want anyone here
see me get heartbroken.

663
00:37:17,713 --> 00:37:18,713
It's not easy.

664
00:37:20,875 --> 00:37:25,502
I was afraid that I'd get
hurt if I gave you everything.

665
00:37:25,847 --> 00:37:28,593
That's probably one of the
reasons why I wasn't straightforward.

666
00:37:30,711 --> 00:37:34,068
I hate to admit it, but
I think I was scared.

667
00:37:37,280 --> 00:37:39,330
(She confesses her
sincere feelings and regret.)

668
00:37:39,355 --> 00:37:41,514
Yes. I was afraid.

669
00:37:42,508 --> 00:37:44,769
- It's a beautiful day.
- Huh?

670
00:37:44,794 --> 00:37:46,532
- It's a beautiful day.
- Yeah.

671
00:37:48,517 --> 00:37:49,517
(Turn)

672
00:37:49,542 --> 00:37:51,753
What's this? What's going on?

673
00:37:52,263 --> 00:37:53,930
Gosh, I can't watch this.

674
00:37:55,888 --> 00:37:57,118
(Turn)

675
00:37:57,143 --> 00:37:59,651
On top of that, Yeo-min was
saying something important.

676
00:37:59,676 --> 00:38:01,209
The weather is so nice.

677
00:38:01,234 --> 00:38:02,916
Yeah, it's really beautiful.

678
00:38:03,594 --> 00:38:04,994
Oh no. What do we do?

679
00:38:05,858 --> 00:38:07,723
Where are they going?

680
00:38:08,939 --> 00:38:11,997
How could they run into
each other like this? Gosh.

681
00:38:14,637 --> 00:38:16,407
They're passing right by them?

682
00:38:16,511 --> 00:38:18,154
Wow, I can't breathe.

683
00:38:19,775 --> 00:38:21,655
(Glance/Turn)

684
00:38:23,730 --> 00:38:25,956
(Da-Na just passed by
as if she didn't see him.)

685
00:38:26,454 --> 00:38:29,744
(Dozens of thoughts
flash through his mind.)

686
00:38:29,769 --> 00:38:31,772
Wow, this is no joke. What do we do?

687
00:38:32,663 --> 00:38:34,416
- Oh no.
- It's making me anxious.

688
00:38:36,017 --> 00:38:37,588
I'm going to close the door.

689
00:38:37,613 --> 00:38:40,257
(She's going on a date
with a different guy.)

690
00:38:40,753 --> 00:38:41,753
Wow, seriously.

691
00:38:42,358 --> 00:38:47,669
This is the cruelest
moment for Yeo-min, isn't it?

692
00:38:47,694 --> 00:38:48,694
Absolutely.

693
00:38:49,961 --> 00:38:52,254
Aren't you guys gonna
meet in the afternoon anyway?

694
00:38:52,847 --> 00:38:54,066
- Later?
- Yeah.

695
00:38:54,567 --> 00:38:56,090
Yes, we are.

696
00:38:57,323 --> 00:38:58,474
(Stare)

697
00:39:00,123 --> 00:39:02,487
We just finished talking but
they're just getting started?

698
00:39:02,945 --> 00:39:06,378
(Is it jealousy? Frustration?
Indescribable emotions strike him.)

699
00:39:06,403 --> 00:39:10,235
What's upsetting is that
Yeo-min was like, "It's

700
00:39:10,260 --> 00:39:13,856
not your fault. I was
scared. I was too late."

701
00:39:13,987 --> 00:39:16,344
She was saying those
things in order to be

702
00:39:16,369 --> 00:39:19,164
considerate towards Won-jae,
who was uncomfortable.

703
00:39:19,189 --> 00:39:21,643
- Right.
- I hope she doesn't blame herself.

704
00:39:21,668 --> 00:39:23,337
She kept blaming
herself since last night.

705
00:39:23,362 --> 00:39:25,209
My heart really breaks.

706
00:39:26,713 --> 00:39:30,262
(Remaining time until the final selection)

707
00:39:32,517 --> 00:39:35,378
(Final Date: Su-won & Ha-neul)

708
00:39:37,079 --> 00:39:39,693
I never knew I'd do flower arrangement.

709
00:39:40,759 --> 00:39:41,957
(Smile)

710
00:39:41,982 --> 00:39:43,809
They're on their way to arrange flowers?

711
00:39:43,834 --> 00:39:45,793
(What did Su-won
plan for their final date?)

712
00:39:46,110 --> 00:39:47,969
This is something that
I've never done before.

713
00:39:47,994 --> 00:39:51,887
I rarely give
flowers to a girl.

714
00:39:52,130 --> 00:39:55,589
I thought it would be more meaningful
if I arranged the flowers myself

715
00:39:56,502 --> 00:39:58,752
and gave them to Ha-neul.

716
00:39:59,396 --> 00:40:00,396
Sounds fun.

717
00:40:00,421 --> 00:40:02,461
I should look up the
meanings of flowers.

718
00:40:02,896 --> 00:40:08,398
I'll look for ones that symbolize
apology, repentance, and enlightenment.

719
00:40:09,036 --> 00:40:10,243
(Grave sinner)

720
00:40:10,268 --> 00:40:11,410
Why is he so cute?

721
00:40:11,435 --> 00:40:13,039
"Enlightenment" is so funny.

722
00:40:13,557 --> 00:40:17,526
I should look for flowers that
symbolize repentance and enlightenment.

723
00:40:18,229 --> 00:40:20,721
- Or separation.
- No, not separation.

724
00:40:20,746 --> 00:40:22,128
- Why not?
- Huh?

725
00:40:23,218 --> 00:40:26,173
Things like "reunion" are fine.

726
00:40:28,303 --> 00:40:30,533
I should ask for flowers like that.

727
00:40:31,925 --> 00:40:35,546
- They're in good spirits again.
- Yeah, they're already like a couple.

728
00:40:37,169 --> 00:40:38,169
Wow!

729
00:40:38,908 --> 00:40:40,774
- It looks nice.
- Flowers!

730
00:40:42,444 --> 00:40:44,428
Wow, it smells really nice.

731
00:40:45,553 --> 00:40:48,394
(A flower shop filled with flowers
of various scents and colors)

732
00:40:49,878 --> 00:40:51,372
Oh my goodness.

733
00:40:53,033 --> 00:40:55,630
- This is the perfect way to
change the mood. - Exactly.

734
00:40:55,655 --> 00:40:57,554
(Will their love be able
to blossom once again?)

735
00:40:57,579 --> 00:41:00,452
Hello, I'll be in charge
of the class today.

736
00:41:00,477 --> 00:41:04,869
We're going to work on a centerpiece,
which is suitable for beginners.

737
00:41:05,565 --> 00:41:08,056
This is what the completed
project will look like.

738
00:41:08,449 --> 00:41:11,035
You'll be able to create
something prettier.

739
00:41:11,413 --> 00:41:15,876
When we do classes
with couples, we use many

740
00:41:15,901 --> 00:41:18,924
beautiful flowers that symbolize "love."

741
00:41:19,246 --> 00:41:22,214
I'll explain what kind of
flowers we have today.

742
00:41:23,122 --> 00:41:26,145
This flower is called "Pasta Gerbera."

743
00:41:26,170 --> 00:41:29,967
It symbolizes mystery and riddles.

744
00:41:30,338 --> 00:41:32,774
And this is a tulip.
Many people look for this.

745
00:41:33,145 --> 00:41:36,142
It looks like a mango, so
it's called a mango tulip.

746
00:41:36,167 --> 00:41:37,961
It symbolizes a love confession.

747
00:41:37,986 --> 00:41:40,765
We prepared three kinds of roses today.

748
00:41:41,270 --> 00:41:46,462
The roses with the biggest faces are
Victorian Secret roses and orange roses.

749
00:41:46,529 --> 00:41:50,782
Many couples love what they symbolize,
which is pure love. It's nice, isn't it?

750
00:41:51,092 --> 00:41:52,659
We're pure. We pure.

751
00:41:53,258 --> 00:41:54,932
This is very meaningful.

752
00:41:55,690 --> 00:41:57,825
And we have wax flowers.

753
00:41:58,081 --> 00:42:01,073
Why don't you try touching
those flowers over there?

754
00:42:01,098 --> 00:42:02,917
- The small ones in the middle.
- These ones?

755
00:42:02,942 --> 00:42:06,626
Yes. Touch them. They feel like
they've been coated in wax, right?

756
00:42:06,896 --> 00:42:07,896
Yes.

757
00:42:07,921 --> 00:42:10,066
(Amazed)

758
00:42:10,091 --> 00:42:12,601
You should pay attention to
the meaning of wax flowers.

759
00:42:12,626 --> 00:42:13,730
What is it?

760
00:42:13,755 --> 00:42:15,709
Fickleness.

761
00:42:16,555 --> 00:42:18,234
(I'm against those flowers...!)

762
00:42:18,259 --> 00:42:21,207
If I were Su-won, I
would take those flowers...

763
00:42:21,706 --> 00:42:23,106
and set them on fire.

764
00:42:23,131 --> 00:42:25,265
- Show her a performance?
- Burn them?

765
00:42:25,690 --> 00:42:26,690
Fickleness.

766
00:42:28,259 --> 00:42:29,259
(Glance)

767
00:42:29,495 --> 00:42:30,892
You should add those in there.

768
00:42:30,917 --> 00:42:33,209
(Sweating)

769
00:42:33,753 --> 00:42:35,220
(Haha)

770
00:42:35,994 --> 00:42:39,044
You can think about
their meanings as you

771
00:42:39,301 --> 00:42:42,091
arrange them and talk
about the ones you like.

772
00:42:43,263 --> 00:42:46,081
It'll be like a message to each other.

773
00:42:50,478 --> 00:42:52,938
Their personalities could
come out while doing this.

774
00:42:52,963 --> 00:42:53,963
What's this?

775
00:42:54,641 --> 00:42:58,355
- Fair flow roses?
- They're multi-headed roses like this.

776
00:42:59,082 --> 00:43:01,240
- Oh, this one?
- Do you like what it symbolizes?

777
00:43:01,265 --> 00:43:02,830
Yes. I like it.

778
00:43:02,855 --> 00:43:06,102
(Fair flow roses: shyness,
confession of first love)

779
00:43:07,306 --> 00:43:11,972
(Su-won's pot is being filled
with flowers that symbolize love.)

780
00:43:13,292 --> 00:43:14,715
(Glance)

781
00:43:17,833 --> 00:43:21,927
Are you looking at the
meanings or just the colors?

782
00:43:21,952 --> 00:43:23,613
I like all the meanings of the flowers.

783
00:43:23,638 --> 00:43:24,838
- Really?
- Yeah.

784
00:43:25,300 --> 00:43:26,833
Do you like fickleness?

785
00:43:27,231 --> 00:43:28,881
Only you should add those in there.

786
00:43:29,161 --> 00:43:31,875
I'll leave that out, and I'll add this.

787
00:43:32,346 --> 00:43:33,632
(He's cute.)

788
00:43:33,657 --> 00:43:35,650
You really can't hate him.

789
00:43:36,208 --> 00:43:39,081
How can I make it look nice?
I want it to be pretty.

790
00:43:39,592 --> 00:43:41,880
I think I'm doing okay.
I'm doing better than I thought.

791
00:43:43,987 --> 00:43:45,423
(Glance)

792
00:43:45,448 --> 00:43:46,591
Not bad.

793
00:43:47,303 --> 00:43:49,536
I'll fill in the empty spots.

794
00:43:50,318 --> 00:43:53,184
(Ha-neul thinks Su-won, who
is praising himself, is adorable.)

795
00:43:53,209 --> 00:43:55,106
He's starting to talk a lot.

796
00:43:55,131 --> 00:43:57,585
(Ha-neul's smile makes Su-won smile along.)

797
00:43:57,610 --> 00:44:00,992
It's my first time doing this.
It doesn't suit me, but I tried to do it.

798
00:44:01,672 --> 00:44:06,561
I've never really given
anyone flowers before.

799
00:44:06,819 --> 00:44:09,462
- Really?
- Yeah.

800
00:44:09,487 --> 00:44:11,274
I really feel like you're not that type.

801
00:44:11,754 --> 00:44:15,238
That's why I thought that if I use
this opportunity to arrange flowers,

802
00:44:16,772 --> 00:44:19,757
it'd be more meaningful.

803
00:44:19,961 --> 00:44:22,485
- Then are you giving that to me?
- Of course.

804
00:44:23,215 --> 00:44:24,670
I'm doing this for you.

805
00:44:24,848 --> 00:44:27,848
Oh, what's this? Things got sweeter again.

806
00:44:30,335 --> 00:44:32,829
- But he's really good at it.
- He's doing a great job.

807
00:44:34,522 --> 00:44:36,038
(Working hard)

808
00:44:36,539 --> 00:44:37,928
Oh, wow.

809
00:44:39,273 --> 00:44:40,741
This is my heart, okay?

810
00:44:40,766 --> 00:44:43,989
The size represents my heart.

811
00:44:44,413 --> 00:44:45,961
I'm just following my heart.

812
00:44:46,914 --> 00:44:48,470
I can't hide it.

813
00:44:48,947 --> 00:44:50,680
His love is overflowing.

814
00:44:51,262 --> 00:44:53,129
This must be my personality.

815
00:44:53,773 --> 00:44:55,796
Yours is huge, but mine isn't.

816
00:44:55,845 --> 00:44:59,353
No. The size of the centerpiece
is the size of your heart.

817
00:45:00,081 --> 00:45:01,081
How sweet.

818
00:45:02,462 --> 00:45:05,400
(Suddenly, Su-won scrutinizes Ha-neul.)

819
00:45:06,476 --> 00:45:09,025
The flowers on your shirt
kind of look like these ones.

820
00:45:09,392 --> 00:45:11,725
- These ones?
- Yes, aren't they like these?

821
00:45:11,750 --> 00:45:12,750
I think so.

822
00:45:14,048 --> 00:45:15,048
There's...

823
00:45:15,587 --> 00:45:19,091
no point wearing flowers on your
shirt when your face is a flower itself.

824
00:45:20,387 --> 00:45:21,538
What's going on?

825
00:45:21,563 --> 00:45:24,683
Su-won usually wasn't the type of
person to make comments like that.

826
00:45:24,708 --> 00:45:26,717
- I know.
- He's being very expressive.

827
00:45:27,291 --> 00:45:30,968
There's no point wearing flowers on your
shirt when your face is a flower itself.

828
00:45:34,070 --> 00:45:35,403
Do you need flowers?

829
00:45:36,723 --> 00:45:39,723
Your face is already a flower.

830
00:45:41,505 --> 00:45:42,806
Why are you laughing?

831
00:45:42,831 --> 00:45:47,832
(Robot Su-won has been
upgraded with "boyfriend" comments.)

832
00:45:48,981 --> 00:45:50,703
- Wow, it's suddenly hot.
- It is!

833
00:45:54,193 --> 00:45:57,193
Oh my. You two have very different styles.

834
00:45:57,218 --> 00:45:58,218
Really?

835
00:45:58,243 --> 00:46:01,849
Please compare your centerpieces to
each other as well as check out the sample.

836
00:46:01,874 --> 00:46:02,874
Okay.

837
00:46:02,899 --> 00:46:04,380
I did refer to that.

838
00:46:04,405 --> 00:46:06,438
(They're clearly very different.)

839
00:46:06,463 --> 00:46:07,932
It's filled with flowers.

840
00:46:07,957 --> 00:46:10,886
You're very wild and greedy, aren't you?

841
00:46:11,703 --> 00:46:12,954
(Guilty)

842
00:46:12,979 --> 00:46:14,246
You're very greedy.

843
00:46:15,201 --> 00:46:16,725
You are really greedy.

844
00:46:17,150 --> 00:46:22,405
This is my heart. I was going to
add more, but I held myself back.

845
00:46:26,269 --> 00:46:28,810
It's beautiful because
there are a bunch of flowers.

846
00:46:28,835 --> 00:46:30,480
It's totally packed.

847
00:46:33,531 --> 00:46:35,635
Ha-neul's centerpiece is really graceful.

848
00:46:35,802 --> 00:46:37,581
- It's pretty.
- It's lovely.

849
00:46:41,063 --> 00:46:43,175
Here I go. One, two, three.

850
00:46:44,432 --> 00:46:46,122
It came out nicely.
You look pretty.

851
00:46:47,164 --> 00:46:49,142
I can't tell which one is the flower.

852
00:46:51,176 --> 00:46:53,243
- It's so hard!
- So adorable.

853
00:46:55,151 --> 00:46:59,263
They're slowly starting to get
back the vibes from the first day.

854
00:47:00,766 --> 00:47:03,570
- What's going on?
- They really do look good together.

855
00:47:03,595 --> 00:47:04,662
Yeah, seriously.

856
00:47:06,542 --> 00:47:08,709
Isn't the weather really nice?

857
00:47:09,868 --> 00:47:11,735
- It's the best.
- Seriously.

858
00:47:13,877 --> 00:47:15,305
Which car are we taking?

859
00:47:15,330 --> 00:47:18,608
- This one. - Wow! I can't believe it.

860
00:47:19,414 --> 00:47:21,614
- Finally.
- It's time to shine.

861
00:47:21,990 --> 00:47:22,990
Let's go.

862
00:47:24,131 --> 00:47:26,354
I'm so curious how this date will turn out.

863
00:47:26,379 --> 00:47:28,635
(They don't have much time.
Can they fill up that gap?)

864
00:47:29,476 --> 00:47:33,194
(They leave the busy city and
go to spend some relaxing time.)

865
00:47:38,593 --> 00:47:41,245
Doesn't this feel like a
couple after they fought?

866
00:47:41,270 --> 00:47:45,176
She's just looking out the
window and he's just driving.

867
00:47:46,483 --> 00:47:49,554
How's the atmosphere for you
guys? Everything's about to end soon.

868
00:47:49,579 --> 00:47:52,295
- It's not that great.
- Right?

869
00:47:55,529 --> 00:47:57,109
They can't keep up a conversation.

870
00:47:58,073 --> 00:47:59,073
Goodness.

871
00:47:59,668 --> 00:48:02,203
- What's going on?
- It's like a goodbye trip.

872
00:48:03,498 --> 00:48:05,580
- Already?
- When they've never hung out before?

873
00:48:05,605 --> 00:48:09,156
If they suddenly became cheerful,
we would've suspected them.

874
00:48:09,823 --> 00:48:12,450
- "They're Money Catchers."
- Right.

875
00:48:15,029 --> 00:48:22,540
Honestly, I thought In-seong
was a Money Catcher.

876
00:48:22,806 --> 00:48:23,806
Really?

877
00:48:24,347 --> 00:48:28,022
I wanted to go on a date
with her and check it out.

878
00:48:29,726 --> 00:48:31,980
He's suspecting her.

879
00:48:32,890 --> 00:48:37,580
I think Jung-woo's
elimination is affecting me.

880
00:48:37,981 --> 00:48:39,774
Jae-hyung approached me so suddenly.

881
00:48:41,128 --> 00:48:42,659
It was out of the blue,

882
00:48:42,787 --> 00:48:47,387
so I don't know if his feelings are
sincere and what my feelings are.

883
00:48:48,445 --> 00:48:49,881
I'm confused.

884
00:48:50,478 --> 00:48:52,200
Yes, it's a bit sudden.

885
00:48:52,601 --> 00:48:55,534
- I actually have a question.
- What is it?

886
00:48:55,902 --> 00:48:59,699
You asked Da-Na out on a date last time.

887
00:49:00,529 --> 00:49:04,301
I'm kind of thinking about that a lot.

888
00:49:04,757 --> 00:49:09,534
It makes me wonder if you're approaching
me because things didn't work out with her.

889
00:49:10,072 --> 00:49:12,627
I think that just has to do with the order.

890
00:49:12,652 --> 00:49:13,685
The order? I see.

891
00:49:13,710 --> 00:49:18,075
Because at that time, you
were dating someone else.

892
00:49:18,100 --> 00:49:20,801
- Right.
- So I...

893
00:49:20,826 --> 00:49:22,891
- It's the timing.
- The timing is really...

894
00:49:24,086 --> 00:49:27,508
I didn't think of the possibility that you
weren't asking me out because of Jung-woo.

895
00:49:27,533 --> 00:49:29,056
Oh, right.

896
00:49:29,346 --> 00:49:31,536
Well, that's what was happening.

897
00:49:32,064 --> 00:49:34,143
But we happened to get this chance.

898
00:49:35,177 --> 00:49:41,665
If Jung-woo hadn't left, I probably
would've asked Da-Na on another date today.

899
00:49:41,864 --> 00:49:43,040
Right.

900
00:49:43,787 --> 00:49:44,969
You're right.

901
00:49:45,164 --> 00:49:47,434
So I'm really happy today.

902
00:49:49,136 --> 00:49:55,443
After we go on this date, regardless
of what happens, I won't regret it.

903
00:49:56,565 --> 00:49:59,112
That's very convincing.

904
00:50:01,522 --> 00:50:02,959
I just want to trust you.

905
00:50:05,050 --> 00:50:06,050
Goodness.

906
00:50:06,724 --> 00:50:08,057
Why are you sighing?

907
00:50:08,082 --> 00:50:09,323
I'm just...

908
00:50:10,761 --> 00:50:12,150
Goodness.

909
00:50:12,653 --> 00:50:16,073
- I think everyone's thinking this way.
- Right.

910
00:50:16,975 --> 00:50:18,728
Everyone wants to trust the other person.

911
00:50:21,408 --> 00:50:22,550
Goodness.

912
00:50:24,706 --> 00:50:27,300
- We're almost here.
- We are.

913
00:50:27,325 --> 00:50:29,804
(A calm and peaceful
sea not too far from Seoul)

914
00:50:31,537 --> 00:50:35,362
(It feels like the sound of the cool waves
will wash away their complicated feelings.)

915
00:50:35,765 --> 00:50:37,050
Thanks.

916
00:50:40,650 --> 00:50:42,864
Wow, it's wonderful.

917
00:50:44,743 --> 00:50:46,195
Wow, it's really beautiful.

918
00:50:47,399 --> 00:50:49,808
(Eurwangni Beach)

919
00:50:49,833 --> 00:50:51,700
- The atmosphere is really nice.
- Yeah.

920
00:50:52,821 --> 00:50:54,354
It's seriously so nice.

921
00:50:54,379 --> 00:50:57,292
(Will the two of them get
closer like a slow rising tide?)

922
00:50:58,286 --> 00:51:01,137
(Feeling the sea breeze,
they walk along the shore.)

923
00:51:04,310 --> 00:51:06,915
- I can't believe we're actually here.
- I know.

924
00:51:07,751 --> 00:51:11,607
- It's nice.
- It was just an idea, but we're here.

925
00:51:13,392 --> 00:51:15,455
- It's seriously so nice.
- It is.

926
00:51:15,480 --> 00:51:17,323
The air feels different, too.

927
00:51:20,598 --> 00:51:21,804
(Hesitate)

928
00:51:22,057 --> 00:51:23,893
I think it's nice because
I'm here with you.

929
00:51:25,625 --> 00:51:26,858
- What?
- My goodness.

930
00:51:27,073 --> 00:51:28,358
It's too out of the blue.

931
00:51:28,383 --> 00:51:30,233
Isn't that out of nowhere?

932
00:51:30,258 --> 00:51:34,315
Maybe he's just trying his best.
Why do I feel like he's being sincere?

933
00:51:35,256 --> 00:51:37,060
I think it's nice because
I'm here with you.

934
00:51:38,212 --> 00:51:40,180
That's so straightforward.

935
00:51:41,492 --> 00:51:43,025
(You're making me shy.)

936
00:51:43,241 --> 00:51:46,296
- That shell is pretty, right?
- Yeah, it is.

937
00:51:46,328 --> 00:51:48,854
(Maybe she's shy. She
switches the topic, and he

938
00:51:48,879 --> 00:51:51,250
plays along so that she
won't be embarrassed.)

939
00:51:51,647 --> 00:51:53,687
Let's each take a shell.

940
00:51:53,712 --> 00:51:55,417
- A pretty one.
- Okay.

941
00:51:55,969 --> 00:51:57,731
There was one that caught my eye.

942
00:51:59,480 --> 00:52:00,813
Which one is pretty?

943
00:52:02,849 --> 00:52:04,381
- Try to find it.
- I will.

944
00:52:04,406 --> 00:52:05,619
I'll look for it here.

945
00:52:06,590 --> 00:52:10,098
(Jae-hyung stopped, and
In-seong is getting farther away.)

946
00:52:10,123 --> 00:52:11,420
This one's broken.

947
00:52:14,103 --> 00:52:17,219
- He's writing something.
- What is he writing?

948
00:52:19,565 --> 00:52:20,565
(Startled)

949
00:52:22,909 --> 00:52:24,116
Out of nowhere?

950
00:52:24,466 --> 00:52:27,237
- What is it?
- What did he do? I'm curious!

951
00:52:27,262 --> 00:52:28,729
- Show us!
- Show us!

952
00:52:29,536 --> 00:52:30,774
What do you think?

953
00:52:31,330 --> 00:52:32,536
(Flustered/Proud)

954
00:52:32,561 --> 00:52:33,561
(In-seong)

955
00:52:35,231 --> 00:52:36,831
Wow, it feels really strange.

956
00:52:38,025 --> 00:52:40,719
(In-seong with a heart?)

957
00:52:40,744 --> 00:52:43,024
Why am I having a mental breakdown?

958
00:52:43,526 --> 00:52:44,526
What's happening?

959
00:52:45,090 --> 00:52:48,711
He suddenly fell hard for In-seong?

960
00:52:49,048 --> 00:52:52,231
When we come next time, we'll be able
to add a name to the other side, right?

961
00:52:54,553 --> 00:52:55,831
It's suddenly hot.

962
00:52:57,477 --> 00:52:59,040
It's hot. It's hot.

963
00:53:03,024 --> 00:53:06,452
After the date, I was really confused.

964
00:53:06,774 --> 00:53:11,115
I don't know how I exactly feel,

965
00:53:11,947 --> 00:53:15,525
and I remembered things
that happened in the pat.

966
00:53:16,117 --> 00:53:18,863
I don't know how I or Jae-hyung feels.

967
00:53:21,210 --> 00:53:23,448
- Our shirts match, too.
- I know.

968
00:53:23,473 --> 00:53:25,346
Anyone can tell that.

969
00:53:26,278 --> 00:53:28,011
I wanted to make a memory.

970
00:53:28,869 --> 00:53:33,806
We've never suspected Jae-hyung
of being a Money Catcher, right?

971
00:53:33,831 --> 00:53:34,905
I don't think so.

972
00:53:34,930 --> 00:53:37,510
It all fits now.

973
00:53:38,156 --> 00:53:42,793
Jae-hyung came as a
Money Catcher but fell in love!

974
00:53:43,463 --> 00:53:46,512
- With Da-Na. - And then he went
back to being a Money Catcher?

975
00:53:46,537 --> 00:53:49,712
When she rejected him, he went
back to being a Money Catcher.

976
00:53:50,835 --> 00:53:53,288
That's possible. You're convincing!

977
00:53:53,313 --> 00:53:56,077
- Right.
- What about In-seong?

978
00:53:56,341 --> 00:54:00,247
I had always suspected
In-seong of being a Money Catcher.

979
00:54:00,272 --> 00:54:03,560
And she kept saying, "Goodness."

980
00:54:03,585 --> 00:54:04,585
It's a bit...

981
00:54:04,610 --> 00:54:06,635
What would she say after "goodness"?

982
00:54:06,660 --> 00:54:09,355
- "Goodness..."
- "I got caught."

983
00:54:11,506 --> 00:54:13,531
(Goodness... In-seong got caught by Loco?)

984
00:54:13,556 --> 00:54:15,605
(Remaining time until the final selection)

985
00:54:15,630 --> 00:54:17,735
- Are you religious?
- I'm not.

986
00:54:17,760 --> 00:54:18,760
Oh, that's good.

987
00:54:19,725 --> 00:54:22,764
I was worried that you were religious.

988
00:54:23,323 --> 00:54:25,536
- Because we're going to a temple.
- I'd still go.

989
00:54:25,914 --> 00:54:31,032
I feel at peace when I go to Bongeunsa.

990
00:54:31,221 --> 00:54:32,681
Oh, Bongeunsa.

991
00:54:33,319 --> 00:54:36,771
It's nice to go there at
night to clear your mind.

992
00:54:37,113 --> 00:54:38,446
I go there at night.

993
00:54:38,705 --> 00:54:40,482
I sometimes just lie down and space out.

994
00:54:40,507 --> 00:54:45,055
- I like things like that. I love them.
- Really?

995
00:54:45,505 --> 00:54:46,886
The atmosphere is nice.

996
00:54:47,515 --> 00:54:50,983
I love incense. I burn incense at home.

997
00:54:51,695 --> 00:54:55,508
The smell is nice, too, but...

998
00:54:55,680 --> 00:54:57,889
- The mood.
- I love the way it burns.

999
00:54:57,914 --> 00:55:02,280
- Yes, exactly! - The way the
smoke goes up like this is pretty.

1000
00:55:03,762 --> 00:55:04,762
Game over.

1001
00:55:04,787 --> 00:55:07,121
Da-Na looks brighter with him.

1002
00:55:07,862 --> 00:55:14,212
Honestly, I was really nervous while
preparing to go on a date with you.

1003
00:55:14,237 --> 00:55:15,527
I don't know why though.

1004
00:55:16,195 --> 00:55:17,943
- Why are you nervous?
- I have no idea.

1005
00:55:17,968 --> 00:55:18,968
Why are you nervous?

1006
00:55:19,555 --> 00:55:21,222
I don't know. I just was.

1007
00:55:23,983 --> 00:55:28,316
I was nervous, but I loosened
up right away while talking to you.

1008
00:55:29,163 --> 00:55:30,763
I feel comfortable, too.

1009
00:55:32,027 --> 00:55:33,027
Thanks.

1010
00:55:35,589 --> 00:55:37,462
I like comfort.

1011
00:55:38,617 --> 00:55:43,291
Ji-min is finally expressing his thoughts.

1012
00:55:43,387 --> 00:55:44,851
Da-Na said she feels comfortable.

1013
00:55:44,876 --> 00:55:48,592
She didn't really say
that to Won-jae, right?

1014
00:55:48,617 --> 00:55:51,417
She just said "thank you."
She didn't say it was nice or anything.

1015
00:55:51,949 --> 00:55:52,949
Poor Won-jae.

1016
00:55:53,916 --> 00:55:56,662
(Meanwhile...)

1017
00:55:56,687 --> 00:55:58,405
Goodness. Poor thing.

1018
00:55:58,676 --> 00:56:00,209
He'd endlessly waiting.

1019
00:56:00,234 --> 00:56:02,814
He just had to see them going out together.

1020
00:56:03,222 --> 00:56:04,690
It must be bugging him.

1021
00:56:06,431 --> 00:56:11,202
(Remaining time until the final selection)

1022
00:56:11,227 --> 00:56:12,443
Time's going by quickly.

1023
00:56:12,468 --> 00:56:13,946
Oh no, the time.

1024
00:56:14,263 --> 00:56:16,430
He should sleep to make the time to faster.

1025
00:56:17,857 --> 00:56:19,436
He must be so uneasy.

1026
00:56:22,607 --> 00:56:25,188
- We're at Bongeunsa!
- It's my first time coming here.

1027
00:56:25,299 --> 00:56:26,699
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

1028
00:56:26,953 --> 00:56:29,446
- There's this one area I like.
- Really?

1029
00:56:29,471 --> 00:56:32,369
- Yes.
- Da-Na chose this date spot.

1030
00:56:32,394 --> 00:56:33,879
Bongeunsa is a nice place.

1031
00:56:34,358 --> 00:56:36,382
- My heart feels at peace.
- Really?

1032
00:56:36,933 --> 00:56:40,044
- The smell of incense makes
you feel at ease. - Exactly.

1033
00:56:41,295 --> 00:56:43,898
I probably make 100 wishes
every time I come here.

1034
00:56:45,494 --> 00:56:47,727
But these two look
really nice together, too.

1035
00:56:49,493 --> 00:56:52,850
- Have you ever walked here before?
- No, it's my first time.

1036
00:56:52,875 --> 00:56:54,536
I didn't even know it existed.

1037
00:56:55,189 --> 00:56:56,911
So there was a place like this.

1038
00:56:58,106 --> 00:57:00,344
- That's an adorable cat!
- Yeah.

1039
00:57:02,269 --> 00:57:04,658
- This is nice.
- I know.

1040
00:57:05,938 --> 00:57:08,447
Gosh, it's so nice. There's a breeze.

1041
00:57:09,554 --> 00:57:11,626
I feel like they'll naturally hold hands.

1042
00:57:12,192 --> 00:57:14,534
- They look good together.
- They're so natural.

1043
00:57:17,929 --> 00:57:21,746
I'm starting to calm down.

1044
00:57:21,771 --> 00:57:23,725
Really? That's great.

1045
00:57:25,119 --> 00:57:26,357
Wow, it's huge!

1046
00:57:29,363 --> 00:57:31,139
- It's really wonderful, isn't it?
- Yeah!

1047
00:57:31,164 --> 00:57:35,522
When I'm feeling down, I come here often.

1048
00:57:35,547 --> 00:57:39,908
When you come here at night, the wind
blows and everything looks transparent.

1049
00:57:40,260 --> 00:57:42,809
- It's so beautiful.
- It's really nice.

1050
00:57:44,162 --> 00:57:48,750
- And I sit here often.
- Really? It's great.

1051
00:57:50,669 --> 00:57:52,685
- Wanna sit down?
- Here?

1052
00:57:52,710 --> 00:57:53,710
Yeah.

1053
00:57:54,945 --> 00:58:01,254
(They quietly sit down and gaze
at the scenery of Bongeunsa.)

1054
00:58:01,856 --> 00:58:05,792
Don't you feel comforted
looking at this kind of view?

1055
00:58:05,817 --> 00:58:07,748
Yeah, just looking at it
makes me feel that way.

1056
00:58:07,773 --> 00:58:09,496
I like the sound of birds chirping, too.

1057
00:58:11,223 --> 00:58:15,287
I think you'll feel pleased if you're at
your favorite place with someone you like.

1058
00:58:16,259 --> 00:58:18,283
You don't come here only
when you're upset, do you?

1059
00:58:18,308 --> 00:58:21,595
- You come here when you're
happy, too, right? - Right.

1060
00:58:21,756 --> 00:58:23,598
When was the last time you came here?

1061
00:58:24,729 --> 00:58:26,777
About a month ago?
I was in the middle of a stroll.

1062
00:58:26,802 --> 00:58:30,669
- I drop by often when I'm walking my dog.
- You walk your dog here?

1063
00:58:30,694 --> 00:58:31,694
Yeah.

1064
00:58:31,934 --> 00:58:34,658
Do you always come here alone?
Do you come with your friends or...?

1065
00:58:36,218 --> 00:58:37,559
- I mostly come alone.
- Really?

1066
00:58:37,591 --> 00:58:39,679
Yeah, it's comfortable that way.

1067
00:58:39,704 --> 00:58:42,871
Am I the first guy you came here with?

1068
00:58:44,758 --> 00:58:46,011
- Yeah.
- Really?

1069
00:58:46,036 --> 00:58:47,036
Yeah.

1070
00:58:47,061 --> 00:58:49,610
- There was a brief silence, wasn't there?
- Yes.

1071
00:58:49,938 --> 00:58:51,129
Dot. Dot. Dot.

1072
00:58:51,154 --> 00:58:53,105
Am I the first guy you came here with?

1073
00:58:54,570 --> 00:58:55,871
- Yeah.
- Really?

1074
00:58:55,896 --> 00:58:56,896
Yeah.

1075
00:58:56,921 --> 00:58:58,912
I see. That's meaningful.

1076
00:58:58,937 --> 00:59:02,204
(Ji-min wanted to be
Da-na's first healing mate.)

1077
00:59:03,056 --> 00:59:05,194
If I'm here, I think I could
space out for 30 minutes.

1078
00:59:05,219 --> 00:59:06,219
I agree.

1079
00:59:07,144 --> 00:59:08,845
(Remaining time until the final selection)

1080
00:59:08,870 --> 00:59:12,522
(Won-jae is spending the same time in
a different place with different feelings.)

1081
00:59:12,547 --> 00:59:14,549
- This time is so...
- Won-jae!

1082
00:59:14,574 --> 00:59:16,980
She promised.

1083
00:59:17,218 --> 00:59:19,578
To meet him early and come back early.

1084
00:59:19,603 --> 00:59:21,017
Oh my gosh.

1085
00:59:21,965 --> 00:59:28,690
(Remaining time until the final selection)

1086
00:59:28,916 --> 00:59:31,384
There's not much time left.

1087
00:59:31,610 --> 00:59:34,268
At this point, you
have to text or call her!

1088
00:59:34,469 --> 00:59:36,651
- Interrupt them.
- That's right!

1089
00:59:37,464 --> 00:59:42,705
(Desire to not pressure her.
Greed to see her. Fear of losing her.)

1090
00:59:43,801 --> 00:59:46,686
(Won-jae, who struggled with
complex feelings, writes another text.)

1091
00:59:46,711 --> 00:59:48,219
He's texting her.

1092
00:59:49,095 --> 00:59:53,733
(If you get a chance to be alone or use
the restroom, can you give me a call?)

1093
00:59:54,330 --> 00:59:56,085
(Hesitate)

1094
00:59:56,522 --> 01:00:00,159
(He can't bring himself
to push the "send" button.)

1095
01:00:03,595 --> 01:00:05,587
- He sent it.
- He sent the text?

1096
01:00:07,295 --> 01:00:11,379
(The alarm echoes in the quiet Bongeunsa.)

1097
01:00:13,541 --> 01:00:16,294
(Bothered)

1098
01:00:18,571 --> 01:00:22,101
(Da-Na checks the message.)

1099
01:00:26,914 --> 01:00:28,311
She didn't reply.

1100
01:00:28,454 --> 01:00:30,439
What do we do? What
do we do? What do we do?

1101
01:00:30,464 --> 01:00:33,965
Everyone is not replying right away in
order to be polite towards their dates.

1102
01:00:34,136 --> 01:00:36,676
Da-Na tends to focus on the
person she's with, doesn't she?

1103
01:00:36,701 --> 01:00:37,701
Yes.

1104
01:00:38,564 --> 01:00:41,211
(He's just like Ji-min who
couldn't fall asleep until dawn.)

1105
01:00:41,545 --> 01:00:43,763
Won-jae is dying right now.

1106
01:00:45,926 --> 01:00:46,926
(Throw)

1107
01:00:51,004 --> 01:00:55,052
This is like "Architecture 101"
with the experienced guy and...

1108
01:00:56,961 --> 01:00:58,310
This is so sad!

1109
01:00:58,476 --> 01:01:01,526
What if the next scene is
Won-jae at Bongeunsa alone?

1110
01:01:02,077 --> 01:01:03,363
Oh my goodness.

1111
01:01:04,701 --> 01:01:07,413
(Won-jae has no idea where
they are or what they're doing.)

1112
01:01:07,438 --> 01:01:09,576
I feel frustrated just watching this.

1113
01:01:09,690 --> 01:01:10,690
For real.

1114
01:01:10,903 --> 01:01:14,207
- I'm sure it's agonizing.
- What will he do?

1115
01:01:15,537 --> 01:01:17,236
I really feel strange right now.

1116
01:01:17,782 --> 01:01:20,275
I'm not mad or furious.

1117
01:01:21,862 --> 01:01:23,234
I'm just so frustrated...

1118
01:01:27,446 --> 01:01:29,811
My head is filling up with bad ideas.

1119
01:01:29,836 --> 01:01:32,695
- Oh, he's anxious.
- I'm sure he is.

1120
01:01:33,596 --> 01:01:35,397
Wanna go get something to drink? It's hot.

1121
01:01:35,588 --> 01:01:36,960
Sure. Let's go.

1122
01:01:39,086 --> 01:01:41,737
What do you usually
drink when you're at a cafe?

1123
01:01:43,361 --> 01:01:46,361
I can't drink coffee,
so I usually get decaf.

1124
01:01:46,530 --> 01:01:48,204
Oh, I see. Or tea?

1125
01:01:48,562 --> 01:01:51,334
Yeah. I get sick when
I drink iced Americano.

1126
01:01:51,631 --> 01:01:52,631
Really?

1127
01:01:53,205 --> 01:01:54,893
But I can't quit drinking.

1128
01:01:56,080 --> 01:01:57,985
It doesn't seem like you drink often.

1129
01:01:58,010 --> 01:01:59,240
Yeah, maybe once a week?

1130
01:01:59,265 --> 01:02:00,813
- I see.
- How much do you drink?

1131
01:02:02,285 --> 01:02:05,793
About 4 days a week?
I drink some before bed.

1132
01:02:07,393 --> 01:02:08,567
(Hehe)

1133
01:02:10,795 --> 01:02:12,167
- We...
- Hmm?

1134
01:02:13,805 --> 01:02:14,872
- "We"?
- "We"?

1135
01:02:17,221 --> 01:02:22,259
Once the sun goes down a
little, should we go grab a drink?

1136
01:02:24,260 --> 01:02:27,411
Wow, no way! Ji-min is just something else!

1137
01:02:27,436 --> 01:02:28,703
Wow, I respect him!

1138
01:02:29,250 --> 01:02:30,742
Should we go grab a drink?

1139
01:02:31,816 --> 01:02:32,816
Really?

1140
01:02:35,327 --> 01:02:37,764
- Oh no. This is crazy.
- What will she say?

1141
01:02:38,626 --> 01:02:41,593
- Oh no.
- Oh no! Won-jae!

1142
01:02:42,883 --> 01:02:43,883
(Stand)

1143
01:02:47,897 --> 01:02:52,134
(He washes his face and picks his outfit.)

1144
01:02:53,958 --> 01:02:55,418
Is he going out?

1145
01:02:56,148 --> 01:02:58,437
- Where is he going?
- To pick her up?

1146
01:02:58,702 --> 01:03:01,968
- Oh, I think he is.
- 'Cause he wants to see her asap?

1147
01:03:03,627 --> 01:03:05,302
Should we go grab a drink?

1148
01:03:05,327 --> 01:03:09,740
(The man I'm comfortable with
VS. the man who's waiting for me)

1149
01:03:09,765 --> 01:03:13,825
(Da-Na finds this situation where
she has to reject someone difficult.)

1150
01:03:14,349 --> 01:03:16,415
- Do you have plans tonight?
- Yes.

1151
01:03:17,436 --> 01:03:19,833
Oh, really? Okay then. What
time do you have to be there?

1152
01:03:19,858 --> 01:03:22,533
I think I need to reply to him right now.

1153
01:03:22,558 --> 01:03:23,558
Oh, really?

1154
01:03:23,800 --> 01:03:25,466
Ah, so you didn't decide the time yet.

1155
01:03:25,491 --> 01:03:26,491
Yeah.

1156
01:03:28,539 --> 01:03:30,318
She was continuously
concerned about Won-jae.

1157
01:03:30,343 --> 01:03:33,259
(Da-Na is thinking, and Ji-min
is watching her nervously.)

1158
01:03:37,648 --> 01:03:39,441
This feels really odd.

1159
01:03:41,133 --> 01:03:42,840
It's really weird.

1160
01:03:44,385 --> 01:03:47,368
(An indescribable feeling)

1161
01:03:47,594 --> 01:03:50,539
But the date time...

1162
01:03:53,699 --> 01:03:57,117
Do you want to ask him? If it's okay, you
can spend one or two hours more with me...

1163
01:03:58,526 --> 01:04:00,994
He wants her to stay longer.
It's a winning move.

1164
01:04:01,602 --> 01:04:03,490
Ji-min isn't giving up.

1165
01:04:03,515 --> 01:04:06,755
Depending on her answer...

1166
01:04:06,780 --> 01:04:09,328
(Perhaps Da-na's answer will
determine her final selection.)

1167
01:04:09,353 --> 01:04:11,116
(Thinking)

1168
01:04:12,915 --> 01:04:14,182
I was very nervous.

1169
01:04:14,870 --> 01:04:19,362
Whether she would go or not depended
on which one of us she likes more.

1170
01:04:20,059 --> 01:04:22,638
If she rejected me now,
it was game over for me.

1171
01:04:23,308 --> 01:04:25,879
Wow, I'm amazed that Ji-min said that.

1172
01:04:26,025 --> 01:04:28,773
It's obvious that Won-jae
is waiting for her, and

1173
01:04:28,798 --> 01:04:31,651
she even promised to go
on a date with him afterward.

1174
01:04:32,585 --> 01:04:36,634
(This relationship will only
end if someone gets hurt.)

1175
01:04:37,982 --> 01:04:41,592
Even if she goes to Won-jae now,
she won't be able to focus on him!

1176
01:04:41,617 --> 01:04:44,819
(The last time that only two people
will be granted before the final selection)

1177
01:04:44,844 --> 01:04:47,456
(Who is Da-na's heart heading towards?)

1178
01:04:55,428 --> 01:04:57,999
Why can't I make up my mind?

1179
01:05:03,485 --> 01:05:06,143
It wasn't just one person who told me.

1180
01:05:06,932 --> 01:05:08,313
It was...

1181
01:05:09,943 --> 01:05:12,110
What do you think? Are
you glad that you came out?

1182
01:05:13,097 --> 01:05:14,430
I'm glad.

1183
01:05:16,626 --> 01:05:17,927
Honestly,

1184
01:05:19,117 --> 01:05:21,700
I don't care whether you're a
Love Catcher or a Money Catcher.

1185
01:05:22,728 --> 01:05:25,838
Thanks for spending
such a fun time with me.

1186
01:05:26,430 --> 01:05:28,263
I have a really good time.

1187
01:05:30,138 --> 01:05:32,313
I'm really grateful
for their hearts, but...

1188
01:05:35,231 --> 01:05:37,192
I don't know what I should do.

1189
01:05:41,595 --> 01:05:43,992
It was too short for me.

1190
01:05:48,302 --> 01:05:50,036
I have no idea how I feel.

1191
01:05:56,477 --> 01:05:58,810
It's because I think too much.

1192
01:05:59,282 --> 01:06:01,869
But I'm going to be greedy.

1193
01:06:04,540 --> 01:06:06,199
Everything was truly wonderful.

1194
01:06:07,695 --> 01:06:09,687
That's why I was very confused.

1195
01:06:12,440 --> 01:06:14,114
From the moment I came here until now,

1196
01:06:15,195 --> 01:06:20,488
no one touched my heart
more than Su-won did.

1197
01:06:23,027 --> 01:06:24,154
Are you ready?
